46
00:03:14,840 --> 00:03:16,120
Look at me.

47
00:03:16,840 --> 00:03:18,360
What happened?

48
00:03:22,320 --> 00:03:24,640
Ateş? Is everything okay?

49
00:03:26,600 --> 00:03:28,440
Yes, everything’s fine.

50
00:03:30,960 --> 00:03:32,960
Doesn’t really seem like it.

51
00:03:33,640 --> 00:03:38,520
Well… I was just going to say don’t take too long.

52
00:03:38,600 --> 00:03:40,360
We don’t have time. We need to go.

53
00:03:40,440 --> 00:03:42,080
Alright, I know.

54
00:03:42,200 --> 00:03:43,840
We already talked about this.

55
00:03:44,280 --> 00:03:47,240
I just have a quick thing to handle. It won’t take long.

56
00:03:47,400 --> 00:03:49,480
I’m glad we’re on the same page.

57
00:04:06,000 --> 00:04:07,600
Are… Are you okay?

58
00:04:10,280 --> 00:04:11,600
Yes. I am.

59
00:04:12,720 --> 00:04:13,960
I mean--

60
00:04:15,760 --> 00:04:17,000
Why are you asking?

61
00:04:17,560 --> 00:04:18,960
You’re acting strange.

62
00:04:19,920 --> 00:04:21,920
I just reminded you we’re in a hurry.

63
00:04:22,960 --> 00:04:24,280
Are you sure?

64
00:04:25,920 --> 00:04:27,560
I also hugged the woman I love.

65
00:04:28,200 --> 00:04:29,920
What’s strange about that?

66
00:04:30,680 --> 00:04:32,320
I guess it just felt that way.

67
00:04:33,480 --> 00:04:37,200
Since we’re in a hurry, let me finish this quickly.

68
00:04:50,760 --> 00:04:53,880
Should I print these documents? Do you think we’ll need them?

69
00:04:58,480 --> 00:05:01,320
Ateş. I asked you a question.

70
00:05:02,440 --> 00:05:03,680
What?

71
00:05:06,720 --> 00:05:08,080
Are you sure you’re okay?

72
00:05:09,320 --> 00:05:10,640
Oh, yeah.

73
00:05:11,520 --> 00:05:12,920
I’ll go check on Cemal.

74
00:05:42,880 --> 00:05:44,560
What's his temperature, mom?

75
00:05:45,640 --> 00:05:46,880
Forty.

76
00:05:47,080 --> 00:05:48,840
Forty?

77
00:05:49,160 --> 00:05:52,520
That’s really high, mom. Should we take him to the hospital?

78
00:05:58,360 --> 00:06:00,200
Go prepare vinegar water right now.

79
00:06:00,280 --> 00:06:03,240
If it doesn’t go down, we’ll take him to the emergency.

80
00:06:03,600 --> 00:06:05,640
Okay.

81
00:06:10,200 --> 00:06:11,640
Çiçek…

82
00:06:14,080 --> 00:06:15,320
Çiçek…

83
00:06:15,480 --> 00:06:17,600
Oh my poor boy! You’re burning up,

84
00:06:17,680 --> 00:06:19,880
and you're still calling Çiçek.

85
00:06:21,200 --> 00:06:25,040
Çiçek… Çiçek.

86
00:06:26,520 --> 00:06:28,120
Here, I brought.

87
00:06:35,560 --> 00:06:37,040
Put it here.

88
00:06:53,560 --> 00:06:54,840
Çiçek.

89
00:06:55,200 --> 00:06:56,760
Oh, Malik.

90
00:07:12,000 --> 00:07:14,000
Please don’t leave me.

91
00:07:28,120 --> 00:07:29,400
Welcome.

92
00:07:35,720 --> 00:07:37,360
Who put this inside the mansion?

93
00:07:38,960 --> 00:07:41,160
How would I know? Why are you asking me?

94
00:07:41,680 --> 00:07:44,000
Someone deliberately put this photo in my room!

95
00:07:48,880 --> 00:07:50,320
Someone set me up!

96
00:07:51,360 --> 00:07:55,200
Only two people could’ve done it! You or Mother Müzeyyen!

97
00:07:56,600 --> 00:07:58,240
Don’t you ever--

98
00:07:58,800 --> 00:08:01,280
Don’t you ever try to play games like this again!

99
00:08:03,440 --> 00:08:04,880
Don’t stand against me.

100
00:08:05,880 --> 00:08:07,480
This is no joke.

101
00:08:09,480 --> 00:08:10,920
I won’t show mercy!

102
00:08:13,440 --> 00:08:16,360
If I’d done it, I’d say I did!

103
00:08:17,320 --> 00:08:18,360
But I didn’t!

104
00:08:19,960 --> 00:08:23,120
Besides… this photo was in the basement.

105
00:08:23,840 --> 00:08:26,200
And no one but you is allowed in there.

106
00:08:27,320 --> 00:08:28,920
Because you have the key.

107
00:08:29,400 --> 00:08:31,120
Come on, Ateş, just calm down.

108
00:08:31,280 --> 00:08:34,800
I remember when Mother Müzeyyen wrecked everything in the basement.

109
00:08:34,880 --> 00:08:37,880
Aslı’s file fell too.

110
00:08:37,960 --> 00:08:40,040
The photo probably got mixed in.

111
00:08:40,520 --> 00:08:42,120
I hope that’s the case.

112
00:08:43,800 --> 00:08:45,640
Otherwise things will change…

113
00:08:46,600 --> 00:08:48,400
… for everyone.

114
00:09:01,120 --> 00:09:04,160
I’m tired of the games Mother Müzeyyen and Aslı play.

115
00:09:04,320 --> 00:09:06,160
Mercan almost saw the photo.

116
00:09:12,640 --> 00:09:14,680
She shouldn’t learn the truth like this.

117
00:09:18,440 --> 00:09:19,840
She should hear it from me.

118
00:09:21,320 --> 00:09:23,560
I’m waiting for the right moment to talk.

119
00:09:25,200 --> 00:09:27,360
But I don’t even know how to do it, Cemal.

120
00:09:29,640 --> 00:09:32,160
I can’t think of anything either.

121
00:09:32,720 --> 00:09:34,320
You’re right. It’s hard.

122
00:09:36,120 --> 00:09:37,560
Very hard, Cemal.

123
00:09:40,320 --> 00:09:42,040
How am I supposed to tell her

124
00:09:42,160 --> 00:09:44,600
I’m someone else, that I came here for revenge?

125
00:09:45,600 --> 00:09:48,160
I don’t know how to say something so terrible.

126
00:09:48,840 --> 00:09:52,800
I wish there were an easy way.

127
00:09:53,880 --> 00:09:55,400
But there isn’t.

128
00:09:58,560 --> 00:10:01,040
Mercan will be devastated when she finds out.

129
00:10:02,720 --> 00:10:04,800
And thinking about that destroys me too.

130
00:10:07,640 --> 00:10:09,080
She’s so pure, so innocent.

131
00:10:11,000 --> 00:10:12,800
She doesn’t deserve any of this.

132
00:10:15,200 --> 00:10:17,240
She’s the most innocent one

133
00:10:18,120 --> 00:10:20,120
among all this cruelty.

134
00:10:22,560 --> 00:10:24,800
When she learns the truth, she’ll hate me.

135
00:10:26,240 --> 00:10:29,600
And maybe our story will end before it even begins.

136
00:10:33,840 --> 00:10:36,440
That’s what terrifies me when I think about it.

137
00:10:43,600 --> 00:10:46,440
Today, Mercan and I will either make a brand new start…

138
00:10:49,520 --> 00:10:51,240
or we’ll say goodbye.

139
00:11:32,800 --> 00:11:36,040
I’m standing here with a member of the Yıldırım family!

140
00:11:40,640 --> 00:11:43,800
All this time he walked through snow without leaving a trace.

141
00:11:47,280 --> 00:11:50,280
And he even tried to get information about the Yıldırıms.

142
00:11:50,360 --> 00:11:53,360
Dude, why didn’t you tell us you were Mr. Haydar’s son? Huh?

143
00:11:53,440 --> 00:11:55,000
What was I supposed to do, bro?

144
00:11:55,120 --> 00:11:58,080
Grab a megaphone and shout "I’m Haydar Yıldırım’s son"?

145
00:11:58,160 --> 00:12:01,520
Good morning.

146
00:12:01,600 --> 00:12:03,120
That actually would’ve helped.

147
00:12:03,280 --> 00:12:04,760
It’s not that simple, bro.

148
00:12:07,120 --> 00:12:10,520
Yaşar, whether he tells or not

149
00:12:10,640 --> 00:12:12,200
is a family matter.

150
00:12:12,320 --> 00:12:14,640
It’s none of our business. Okay?

151
00:12:16,520 --> 00:12:18,720
Aren't we practically family too, Ms. Zahide?

152
00:12:21,280 --> 00:12:24,200
You have a very strange understanding of the word family.

153
00:12:24,280 --> 00:12:27,200
Maybe open a dictionary and see what it actually means.

154
00:12:27,520 --> 00:12:29,480
Hah! Listen to her.

155
00:12:30,120 --> 00:12:31,640
Ms. Zahide,

156
00:12:33,640 --> 00:12:37,920
Did you give up on the ponytail?

157
00:12:38,240 --> 00:12:41,320
It looks different but it suits you.

158
00:12:42,280 --> 00:12:45,320
What does that have to do with anything, Yaşar?

159
00:12:45,520 --> 00:12:50,000
The way you jump from topic to topic is dizzying.

160
00:12:50,840 --> 00:12:52,520
Yes, I did it like this today.

161
00:12:54,120 --> 00:12:56,040
She liked that I noticed.

162
00:12:56,120 --> 00:12:58,440
I’ve got an eye for things. I don’t miss much.

163
00:12:58,520 --> 00:13:00,520
I've got visual intelligence.

164
00:13:00,600 --> 00:13:03,560
Yeah, you’ve got some serious visual skills, bro.

165
00:13:03,640 --> 00:13:04,720
Haven't I?

166
00:13:04,880 --> 00:13:06,560
She really liked it. Didn’t she?

167
00:13:06,680 --> 00:13:08,040
Keep it up.

168
00:13:08,480 --> 00:13:10,280
You’re moving slow, though.

169
00:13:30,200 --> 00:13:31,960
Mom, he still feels hot.

170
00:13:32,040 --> 00:13:34,360
Shouldn’t we take him to the hospital?

171
00:13:35,440 --> 00:13:36,680
Let's check it again.

172
00:13:56,640 --> 00:13:59,320
-How is it? -Ah, it dropped a little.

173
00:13:59,680 --> 00:14:02,280
-Really? -So the vinegar water worked.

174
00:14:02,640 --> 00:14:03,920
Good.

175
00:14:04,480 --> 00:14:05,760
Çiçek…

176
00:14:06,160 --> 00:14:07,520
Where are you, Çiçek?

177
00:14:11,160 --> 00:14:12,360
My Çiçek…

178
00:14:14,280 --> 00:14:17,520
My Çiçek… my beautiful one…

179
00:14:18,520 --> 00:14:20,080
Çiçek, you haven't left…

180
00:14:20,800 --> 00:14:23,400
Thank God, he opened his eyes.

181
00:14:38,120 --> 00:14:39,640
Lie down, son.

182
00:14:39,760 --> 00:14:41,880
You’re burning up.

183
00:14:41,960 --> 00:14:43,520
We found you outside.

184
00:14:43,680 --> 00:14:48,160
No, it's not appropriate for me to stay here.

185
00:14:48,480 --> 00:14:49,560
I should go.

186
00:14:49,640 --> 00:14:50,800
Lie down, son.

187
00:14:50,920 --> 00:14:54,440
You don’t even have the strength to move. You’re burning up with fever.

188
00:14:54,520 --> 00:14:57,240
I’ve troubled you enough already.

189
00:14:57,360 --> 00:15:00,040
I can't. It's not right.

190
00:15:00,680 --> 00:15:02,080
You’re no trouble, son.

191
00:15:02,160 --> 00:15:04,560
Illness isn’t anyone’s fault.

192
00:15:05,680 --> 00:15:09,320
Yes, things happened, but that’s different.

193
00:15:10,360 --> 00:15:13,000
You don’t have your parents here to look after you.

194
00:15:13,520 --> 00:15:15,520
We’re not that heartless.

195
00:15:15,960 --> 00:15:17,480
Lie down. Rest.

196
00:15:18,200 --> 00:15:19,600
Thank you.

197
00:15:19,720 --> 00:15:21,280
Really… thank you.

198
00:15:56,560 --> 00:16:00,040
Nothing seems off at the hospital site.

199
00:16:00,600 --> 00:16:03,400
My only worry is not finishing by the date we planned.

200
00:16:04,000 --> 00:16:06,080
Maybe we should bring in extra support?

201
00:16:07,600 --> 00:16:08,960
Ateş.

202
00:16:09,160 --> 00:16:10,600
Yes?

203
00:16:11,680 --> 00:16:13,040
What’s going on with you?

204
00:16:13,160 --> 00:16:15,480
I’m talking and you’re not hearing a word.

205
00:16:15,560 --> 00:16:17,640
You were weird on the way here too.

206
00:16:18,520 --> 00:16:20,400
Nothing’s wrong. I just drifted off.

207
00:16:21,840 --> 00:16:23,160
You can talk to me.

208
00:16:23,840 --> 00:16:25,480
I said nothing’s wrong, Mercan!

209
00:16:25,680 --> 00:16:27,440
Why do you keep asking?

210
00:16:32,640 --> 00:16:34,240
Mercan.

211
00:16:35,920 --> 00:16:38,200
I’m sorry. I didn’t mean to yell.

212
00:16:39,600 --> 00:16:40,920
Let go, I’m leaving.

213
00:16:41,000 --> 00:16:42,560
Mercan, please.

214
00:16:44,360 --> 00:16:45,440
I have work.

215
00:16:45,520 --> 00:16:46,840
I need to…

216
00:16:47,040 --> 00:16:49,200
check the hospital reports. Let go.

217
00:16:49,280 --> 00:16:50,520
Don’t go.

218
00:16:51,640 --> 00:16:53,000
Work here today.

219
00:16:53,920 --> 00:16:55,160
Why?

220
00:16:55,640 --> 00:16:57,360
What am I being punished for now?

221
00:16:59,880 --> 00:17:01,240
It’s not punishment.

222
00:17:03,000 --> 00:17:04,160
It’s a reward.

223
00:17:07,840 --> 00:17:09,600
Something’s been off for days.

224
00:17:10,520 --> 00:17:12,120
I ask, you snap.

225
00:17:12,280 --> 00:17:15,800
You were strange this morning. You raised your voice on the way here.

226
00:17:15,880 --> 00:17:18,720
I let it go, stayed quiet. But--

227
00:17:20,600 --> 00:17:22,120
Just let me go.

228
00:17:45,480 --> 00:17:46,880
Wow,

229
00:17:47,960 --> 00:17:49,880
You’re lucky again, Mrs. Nermin.

230
00:17:50,920 --> 00:17:53,160
God took pity on you.

231
00:17:56,520 --> 00:17:59,280
Gave you a new child in place of the one you lost.

232
00:18:02,240 --> 00:18:04,600
Fully grown, ready-made.

233
00:18:04,680 --> 00:18:06,360
How fortunate for you.

234
00:18:13,840 --> 00:18:15,520
I know what cruelty is,

235
00:18:16,400 --> 00:18:18,640
but I’ve never seen anything like yours.

236
00:18:19,880 --> 00:18:22,440
You’re made of pure hatred from head to toe.

237
00:18:25,800 --> 00:18:28,120
When it comes to losing a child,

238
00:18:28,560 --> 00:18:31,000
people should think twice before they speak.

239
00:18:36,640 --> 00:18:39,120
Drop the innocent act.

240
00:18:39,520 --> 00:18:40,760
You can’t fool me.

241
00:18:41,320 --> 00:18:43,640
I know exactly what you are.

242
00:18:45,880 --> 00:18:47,920
You led my Murat to his death.

243
00:18:49,520 --> 00:18:50,960
I curse you.

244
00:18:51,720 --> 00:18:54,160
And that curse won’t go unanswered.

245
00:18:55,760 --> 00:18:58,280
I will take my revenge, sooner or later.

246
00:18:59,920 --> 00:19:02,600
I haven’t forgotten what you did to my daughter.

247
00:19:03,000 --> 00:19:05,560
If I wanted, I could’ve been as merciless as you.

248
00:19:06,160 --> 00:19:08,120
I could’ve killed her right there.

249
00:19:09,400 --> 00:19:13,280
I didn’t. I showed mercy.

250
00:19:17,600 --> 00:19:21,520
I only wanted you to feel the fear of losing a child.

251
00:19:23,040 --> 00:19:25,160
But now I wish--

252
00:19:32,480 --> 00:19:34,480
Don’t you ever come at me again.

253
00:19:34,800 --> 00:19:37,560
You think I'm an easy prey.

254
00:19:43,160 --> 00:19:44,400
But I'm not.

255
00:20:13,360 --> 00:20:14,840
How is he?

256
00:20:15,600 --> 00:20:18,040
He's better. His fever dropped a little.

257
00:20:19,000 --> 00:20:20,480
-Really? -Mm‑hmm.

258
00:20:25,200 --> 00:20:26,720
Then he can go home.

259
00:20:28,840 --> 00:20:30,200
Don't be ridiculous, son.

260
00:20:30,280 --> 00:20:31,720
He still has a fever.

261
00:20:32,120 --> 00:20:34,360
He has no one to look after him. Go where?

262
00:20:34,560 --> 00:20:37,000
What are we, a clinic?

263
00:20:37,920 --> 00:20:39,160
For God's sake,

264
00:20:39,560 --> 00:20:41,280
when is he supposed to get up?

265
00:20:41,760 --> 00:20:44,080
Let him fully come to himself, let him recover.

266
00:20:44,200 --> 00:20:47,520
Once he’s back on his feet, we’ll send him.

267
00:20:58,200 --> 00:20:59,880
Fine then, Mom.

268
00:21:00,760 --> 00:21:02,000
I bought him medicine.

269
00:21:03,400 --> 00:21:08,400
Give it to him. Let him get better and leave our home as soon as possible.

270
00:21:08,560 --> 00:21:10,880
-Huh? -Yeah. He better goes to his room.

271
00:21:14,640 --> 00:21:16,640
Look at you. You care for him.

272
00:21:17,320 --> 00:21:18,960
How unpredictable you are.

273
00:21:22,040 --> 00:21:24,120
I’m always the unpredictable one, right.

274
00:21:30,680 --> 00:21:33,240
We don’t kick people when they’re down, son.

275
00:21:33,360 --> 00:21:34,880
Did I raise you like this?

276
00:21:39,360 --> 00:21:41,880
Don’t pretend. You care.

277
00:21:42,960 --> 00:21:44,240
Me?

278
00:21:45,240 --> 00:21:46,440
I care?

279
00:21:47,280 --> 00:21:48,640
I care for him?

280
00:21:48,720 --> 00:21:50,080
Look at him.

281
00:21:53,680 --> 00:21:55,800
For God's sake, why would I care for him?

282
00:21:55,920 --> 00:21:57,240
Let him burn.

283
00:21:57,920 --> 00:21:59,400
He fooled us this whole time.

284
00:22:00,200 --> 00:22:02,280
He played us for fools. Completely.

285
00:22:04,040 --> 00:22:07,240
Ugh, why would I care?

286
00:22:10,680 --> 00:22:12,000
I’m leaving.

287
00:22:12,760 --> 00:22:15,120
As if I don’t know you.

288
00:22:36,600 --> 00:22:38,040
Um,

289
00:22:39,400 --> 00:22:41,120
Are you still mad at me, brother?

290
00:22:48,760 --> 00:22:50,080
Why would I be?

291
00:22:50,880 --> 00:22:52,440
You didn’t do anything wrong.

292
00:22:53,200 --> 00:22:55,160
What’s done is done.

293
00:22:56,320 --> 00:23:00,480
But things will get harder from now on.

294
00:23:00,920 --> 00:23:02,080
Be ready.

295
00:23:03,720 --> 00:23:05,600
I’ve been ready since the beginning.

296
00:23:06,120 --> 00:23:09,560
I’ve been ready since the day you found me and offered me this job.

297
00:23:10,280 --> 00:23:12,280
Be careful with Haydar.

298
00:23:14,200 --> 00:23:15,520
Don’t act on your own.

299
00:23:15,640 --> 00:23:17,000
You can’t trust that man.

300
00:23:18,960 --> 00:23:22,360
You’ve suffered enough because of Haydar and Nermin.

301
00:23:23,960 --> 00:23:27,120
Stop thinking about them and focus on learning the business.

302
00:23:27,960 --> 00:23:29,320
When all this is over,

303
00:23:30,680 --> 00:23:32,480
this company will be yours.

304
00:23:33,360 --> 00:23:36,480
You and Mercan will take back everything you deserve.

305
00:23:37,840 --> 00:23:39,280
Thank you, brother.

306
00:23:39,640 --> 00:23:41,400
You made it happen.

307
00:23:50,680 --> 00:23:53,040
I should go.

308
00:23:53,480 --> 00:23:54,600
Burak…

309
00:23:57,840 --> 00:24:00,520
If you’re leaving because I came in, don’t.

310
00:24:01,000 --> 00:24:02,640
I’m leaving soon, anyway.

311
00:24:06,360 --> 00:24:07,520
Um…

312
00:24:08,240 --> 00:24:11,760
I just don’t want to bother you.

313
00:24:13,120 --> 00:24:14,760
You didn’t do anything wrong.

314
00:24:19,360 --> 00:24:22,640
If we’re siblings, then we should be together.

315
00:24:27,760 --> 00:24:30,760
From now on, I want Burak to live with us at the mansion.

316
00:24:39,640 --> 00:24:42,120
I can’t stand the thought of you being alone.

317
00:24:42,880 --> 00:24:44,720
Your place is with your family.

318
00:24:47,720 --> 00:24:49,280
Thank you. I appreciate it.

319
00:24:57,360 --> 00:24:58,520
Mercan! Wait!

320
00:24:58,680 --> 00:24:59,640
What?

321
00:25:01,520 --> 00:25:02,760
Mr. Ateş, we're ready.

322
00:25:03,120 --> 00:25:04,320
Thank you.

323
00:25:06,000 --> 00:25:07,560
-Come with me. -Where?

324
00:25:09,360 --> 00:25:10,200
I said come.

325
00:25:10,880 --> 00:25:12,080
I can’t.

326
00:25:12,640 --> 00:25:13,760
I have work.

327
00:25:14,400 --> 00:25:16,360
-I said move. -I’m not moving.

328
00:25:17,040 --> 00:25:18,640
You’re bullying again.

329
00:25:19,600 --> 00:25:23,800
If you don’t walk, I’ll carry you.

330
00:25:24,200 --> 00:25:25,440
Your choice.

331
00:25:25,680 --> 00:25:28,160
No thanks. No need for that.

332
00:25:37,320 --> 00:25:38,720
Where are you, man?

333
00:25:39,200 --> 00:25:41,400
You disappear like a ghost.

334
00:25:42,080 --> 00:25:43,160
Who were you calling?

335
00:25:44,520 --> 00:25:46,320
It’s about Ateş again, isn’t it?

336
00:25:47,560 --> 00:25:49,280
Let it go.

337
00:25:50,320 --> 00:25:52,320
He’s madly in love with your daughter.

338
00:25:52,720 --> 00:25:55,240
He’s not going to hurt her family.

339
00:25:59,000 --> 00:26:02,920
Are you going to sulk forever?

340
00:26:03,880 --> 00:26:05,680
What was I supposed to do, Haydar?

341
00:26:05,760 --> 00:26:07,560
Accept your mistress?

342
00:26:08,360 --> 00:26:11,240
I stayed silent for years. I endured everything.

343
00:26:12,280 --> 00:26:13,720
Is this my reward?

344
00:26:14,200 --> 00:26:16,160
Then you shouldn’t have endured it!

345
00:26:16,280 --> 00:26:17,480
Who told you to?

346
00:26:17,600 --> 00:26:19,120
You should’ve left!

347
00:26:21,280 --> 00:26:24,640
I’m tired of you throwing this in my face every time we argue!

348
00:26:24,720 --> 00:26:26,520
You chose to stay with me.

349
00:26:26,920 --> 00:26:28,960
Because you loved the power. The money.

350
00:26:29,200 --> 00:26:31,000
Nurgül was different.

351
00:26:31,720 --> 00:26:33,880
She loved only me. Got it?

352
00:26:34,120 --> 00:26:36,080
She didn’t care about power or money.

353
00:26:37,960 --> 00:26:39,760
If she loved you so much,

354
00:26:40,120 --> 00:26:43,120
she shouldn’t have left just because of your single word.

355
00:26:43,200 --> 00:26:45,040
She should’ve stayed and fought.

356
00:26:45,120 --> 00:26:47,760
She kept your son from you.

357
00:26:48,960 --> 00:26:50,120
But, I…

358
00:26:50,400 --> 00:26:52,480
I gave you a son.

359
00:26:52,760 --> 00:26:54,120
I gave you my Murat.

360
00:26:56,200 --> 00:26:58,040
But that woman took your son away.

361
00:27:07,760 --> 00:27:09,080
Murat…

362
00:27:09,280 --> 00:27:11,320
… I never loved him like a son.

363
00:27:11,480 --> 00:27:14,840
If you keep pushing, I’ll say things you won’t recover from.

364
00:27:15,160 --> 00:27:16,480
Step aside.

365
00:27:43,920 --> 00:27:45,200
What is all this?

366
00:27:46,080 --> 00:27:47,760
I had the table set up here.

367
00:27:48,480 --> 00:27:50,040
So I could be alone with you.

368
00:28:02,840 --> 00:28:04,000
I love you so much.

369
00:28:08,520 --> 00:28:11,000
I’m not saying it. You’ll wait forever.

370
00:28:12,720 --> 00:28:14,040
I’ll wait.

371
00:28:14,480 --> 00:28:16,160
Please, have a seat, Mrs. Mercan.

372
00:28:19,920 --> 00:28:22,080
Thank you.

373
00:28:35,160 --> 00:28:38,120
If you think this will make me forgive you, you’re wrong.

374
00:28:39,560 --> 00:28:41,200
I’m not trying to trick you.

375
00:28:41,320 --> 00:28:42,640
I’m apologizing.

376
00:28:42,720 --> 00:28:44,080
You apologized. Fine.

377
00:28:46,120 --> 00:28:48,640
Don’t drag it out. I apologized. That’s it.

378
00:28:49,920 --> 00:28:52,000
Oh, so you apologized and set a table,

379
00:28:52,080 --> 00:28:54,240
and I’m supposed to forgive you instantly?

380
00:28:56,440 --> 00:28:59,680
No. You should’ve thought before yelling.

381
00:29:05,680 --> 00:29:07,440
I know you don’t want to go.

382
00:29:10,680 --> 00:29:11,800
I do.

383
00:29:14,080 --> 00:29:15,440
You know I won’t let you.

384
00:29:18,520 --> 00:29:20,320
I don’t know that at all.

385
00:29:21,120 --> 00:29:22,880
You break hearts too easily.

386
00:29:23,680 --> 00:29:26,280
Come on… you know.

387
00:29:28,760 --> 00:29:31,080
No matter what happens, don’t leave me.

388
00:29:31,960 --> 00:29:33,560
No matter what happens--

389
00:29:55,000 --> 00:29:56,960
Don’t yell at me like that again.

390
00:29:57,520 --> 00:29:58,840
You hurt my feelings.

391
00:29:59,960 --> 00:30:01,120
I never wanted to.

392
00:30:04,040 --> 00:30:05,640
Keep me in your heart.

393
00:30:07,240 --> 00:30:08,520
I will.

394
00:30:11,600 --> 00:30:13,600
This heart will beat with yours…

395
00:30:16,640 --> 00:30:18,080
…until it stops.

396
