406
00:31:17,480 --> 00:31:19,320
You scared me!

407
00:31:21,120 --> 00:31:23,840
Ugh, Berat, you always do this.

408
00:31:24,640 --> 00:31:25,960
What!

409
00:31:26,360 --> 00:31:27,720
Were you scared, my sultan.

410
00:31:27,800 --> 00:31:28,880
Yes!

411
00:31:28,960 --> 00:31:31,160
I only wanted to surprise you.

412
00:31:32,880 --> 00:31:34,920
Is the surprise in that box?

413
00:31:35,720 --> 00:31:37,400
Let’s see if you’ll like it.

414
00:31:40,000 --> 00:31:43,360
Oh my God. I can’t believe it.

415
00:31:44,680 --> 00:31:46,520
You bought me a wedding dress?

416
00:31:47,600 --> 00:31:48,640
Yeah.

417
00:31:49,480 --> 00:31:52,520
Let me see.

418
00:32:04,040 --> 00:32:05,280
How does it look?

419
00:32:06,720 --> 00:32:08,520
It is beautiful, Zehra.

420
00:32:14,280 --> 00:32:15,920
Thank you, Berat.

421
00:32:19,760 --> 00:32:21,400
You really touched my heart.

422
00:32:37,360 --> 00:32:38,520
Zehra…

423
00:32:39,360 --> 00:32:42,040
…you deserve the very best.

424
00:32:55,480 --> 00:32:56,760
Look, Zehra.

425
00:32:57,600 --> 00:32:59,560
I won’t let you go lacking anything.

426
00:33:00,560 --> 00:33:03,320
Everything will be just the way you dreamed.

427
00:33:03,600 --> 00:33:06,520
You’ll cry tears of happiness.

428
00:33:13,080 --> 00:33:15,280
We’ll build a beautiful family together.

429
00:33:31,840 --> 00:33:36,360
I should get going. There’s work waiting.

430
00:33:36,960 --> 00:33:38,120
See you later.

431
00:33:38,560 --> 00:33:39,920
Okay.

432
00:33:40,360 --> 00:33:41,840
-Berat. -Yeah?

433
00:33:43,200 --> 00:33:44,440
I’m glad you exist.

434
00:33:47,440 --> 00:33:50,400
You too, my sultan.

435
00:33:57,440 --> 00:33:58,880
I should go.

436
00:34:00,200 --> 00:34:01,800
Talk to you later.

437
00:34:02,240 --> 00:34:03,800
Oh God.

438
00:34:04,400 --> 00:34:06,520
I’m such a klutz today.

439
00:34:06,640 --> 00:34:07,920
Just today?

440
00:34:08,320 --> 00:34:09,560
-No? -No.

441
00:34:09,680 --> 00:34:11,640
You’re always a klutz.

442
00:34:14,920 --> 00:34:16,560
But that’s how I love you.

443
00:34:28,840 --> 00:34:30,680
-See you.-See you.

444
00:34:37,200 --> 00:34:38,400
It's so beautiful.

445
00:34:44,360 --> 00:34:46,560
Let me put it away before anyone sees.

446
00:35:18,160 --> 00:35:20,160
Neither Mercan nor I are kids.

447
00:35:20,960 --> 00:35:22,800
We don't need your permission.

448
00:35:26,160 --> 00:35:28,000
I won't give up the woman I love

449
00:35:28,840 --> 00:35:30,920
just because you don't approve.

450
00:36:32,280 --> 00:36:33,800
Aslı, what are you doing?

451
00:36:33,880 --> 00:36:35,760
You'll hurt yourself.

452
00:36:36,560 --> 00:36:38,040
You'll injure yourself.

453
00:36:40,000 --> 00:36:42,080
Mercan and Ateş are the ones hurting me.

454
00:36:44,840 --> 00:36:46,960
Don't worry, I know.

455
00:36:51,040 --> 00:36:52,840
And I know what you did, Aslı.

456
00:36:53,680 --> 00:36:55,200
What are you talking about?

457
00:36:57,040 --> 00:36:58,680
The photo in the study.

458
00:36:59,560 --> 00:37:00,880
You put it there.

459
00:37:02,840 --> 00:37:04,760
You’re doing the wrong thing, Aslı.

460
00:37:04,840 --> 00:37:06,960
They’re together now. They love each other.

461
00:37:10,200 --> 00:37:11,360
So?

462
00:37:14,080 --> 00:37:16,400
So things have changed.

463
00:37:18,040 --> 00:37:20,840
Look, Mercan isn’t a target for Ateş anymore.

464
00:37:21,480 --> 00:37:22,880
She’s the woman he loves.

465
00:37:23,880 --> 00:37:25,600
What you’re doing is pure malice.

466
00:37:26,400 --> 00:37:28,360
Malice, huh?

467
00:37:30,080 --> 00:37:31,880
Everything I do, I do for love.

468
00:37:32,560 --> 00:37:34,000
For Ateş.

469
00:37:34,080 --> 00:37:36,240
I say it proudly.

470
00:37:36,600 --> 00:37:37,920
Can you say the same?

471
00:37:38,560 --> 00:37:41,320
It's not about whether I can. I wouldn't do it.

472
00:37:45,120 --> 00:37:49,720
Because, unlike you, I know the difference between love and obsession.

473
00:37:51,240 --> 00:37:53,720
What you feel isn’t love. It’s pure obsession.

474
00:37:55,800 --> 00:37:57,480
Don’t preach to me!

475
00:37:58,480 --> 00:38:01,120
What do you know about love, about passion!

476
00:38:01,880 --> 00:38:04,400
Have you loved anyone the way I love Ateş!

477
00:38:04,800 --> 00:38:07,120
How do you know I haven’t, Aslı?!

478
00:38:08,440 --> 00:38:11,680
You think you know me so well, but you don’t.

479
00:38:12,240 --> 00:38:14,880
I know exactly what love and passion are.

480
00:38:15,840 --> 00:38:17,120
I…

481
00:38:20,920 --> 00:38:22,280
You what?

482
00:38:45,680 --> 00:38:47,240
I… see those two, Aslı.

483
00:38:48,880 --> 00:38:50,280
Mercan loves him too.

484
00:38:57,920 --> 00:38:59,640
Leave Ateş and Mercan alone.

485
00:38:59,920 --> 00:39:02,040
This whole thing is getting really old.

486
00:39:22,200 --> 00:39:24,160
It’s almost evening.

487
00:39:26,880 --> 00:39:28,080
So what.

488
00:39:29,520 --> 00:39:31,880
Let’s stay here. Just the two of us.

489
00:39:32,280 --> 00:39:33,600
In this moment.

490
00:39:34,760 --> 00:39:37,800
If that’s what you want, we’ll stay.

491
00:39:39,040 --> 00:39:40,320
Let's stay for days.

492
00:39:42,200 --> 00:39:43,880
They’ll find us frozen.

493
00:39:45,360 --> 00:39:46,480
Let them.

494
00:39:47,800 --> 00:39:49,880
We’ll be like the Lovers of Alvaro.

495
00:39:50,800 --> 00:39:51,960
You know them, right?

496
00:39:52,040 --> 00:39:54,840
The skeletons found in Italy, still holding each other.

497
00:39:54,920 --> 00:39:57,480
I know. Not even death could separate them.

498
00:39:58,760 --> 00:40:00,360
It can’t separate us either.

499
00:40:00,920 --> 00:40:02,040
…won’t separate us.

500
00:40:06,680 --> 00:40:09,440
Everyone will talk about our love.

501
00:40:13,520 --> 00:40:15,480
When I first saw you, I knew.

502
00:40:18,640 --> 00:40:21,680
On the boat, when I looked at your face for the first time

503
00:40:21,840 --> 00:40:23,840
I said, "This man will be my destiny."

504
00:40:30,640 --> 00:40:33,800
For me it was being struck at first sight.

505
00:40:38,720 --> 00:40:40,320
But it was more than that.

506
00:40:42,440 --> 00:40:43,840
When I saw you, I thought,

507
00:40:43,920 --> 00:40:47,520
"The woman I’ve dreamed of since childhood is right in front of me."

508
00:40:48,880 --> 00:40:50,240
Since childhood?

509
00:40:51,920 --> 00:40:54,320
If they asked me to draw her, I’d draw you.

510
00:40:57,360 --> 00:40:58,720
Your hair,

511
00:40:59,720 --> 00:41:01,120
your eyes,

512
00:41:03,920 --> 00:41:05,560
the innocence in your gaze.

513
00:41:21,240 --> 00:41:22,520
What are you doing?

514
00:41:25,320 --> 00:41:26,840
Saving us from freezing.

515
00:41:35,600 --> 00:41:36,840
Would you dance with me?

516
00:41:40,880 --> 00:41:44,040
Here? Now? What if someone sees?

517
00:41:45,520 --> 00:41:46,960
Let them. So what?

518
00:41:48,080 --> 00:41:49,520
But it’d be inappropriate.

519
00:41:49,840 --> 00:41:51,840
Why? We’re not doing anything wrong.

520
00:41:52,680 --> 00:41:56,680
And I’m the boss. Let me enjoy the perks a little.

521
00:42:00,360 --> 00:42:01,720
So? Will you dance with me?

522
00:44:14,440 --> 00:44:16,760
May our love never end. Okay?

523
00:44:17,960 --> 00:44:21,720
A love this big may never end.

524
00:45:54,560 --> 00:45:57,240
What did you do, Çiçek?

525
00:46:00,280 --> 00:46:02,520
I’m so sorry, Mrs. Nermin.

526
00:46:03,840 --> 00:46:05,320
Look at the carpet!

527
00:46:06,280 --> 00:46:07,440
What now?

528
00:46:07,560 --> 00:46:09,240
I’ll clean it right away.

529
00:46:09,320 --> 00:46:10,920
It won’t stain.

530
00:46:11,360 --> 00:46:14,520
I paid a fortune for this.

531
00:46:14,840 --> 00:46:16,880
What if it leaves a stain?

532
00:46:19,200 --> 00:46:20,960
Can’t you do anything right?

533
00:46:25,360 --> 00:46:28,040
Did we do something wrong, Mrs. Nermin?

534
00:46:28,280 --> 00:46:29,560
This isn’t a mistake.

535
00:46:30,000 --> 00:46:31,480
It’s incompetence.

536
00:46:34,600 --> 00:46:37,840
Look! Look what your daughter did to my beautiful carpet.

537
00:46:41,440 --> 00:46:42,840
Don’t worry, Mrs. Nermin.

538
00:46:42,920 --> 00:46:46,000
I’ll clean it now. It won’t leave a stain.

539
00:46:47,240 --> 00:46:50,040
I had this carpet brought specially.

540
00:46:50,520 --> 00:46:51,800
Look what happened.

541
00:46:53,160 --> 00:46:57,040
Binnaz, clean it properly. I don’t want a single mark left.

542
00:46:57,400 --> 00:46:58,880
Did you understand?

543
00:47:01,000 --> 00:47:02,160
Honestly!

544
00:47:02,720 --> 00:47:04,160
Be careful!

545
00:47:07,080 --> 00:47:10,520
You couldn’t buy this carpet even if you saved a year’s salary!

546
00:47:12,920 --> 00:47:15,760
What is this carelessness? What is this incompetence?

547
00:47:15,840 --> 00:47:17,480
I don't understand.

548
00:47:23,800 --> 00:47:26,120
Oh, Çiçek.

549
00:47:26,680 --> 00:47:29,040
See the difference between rich and poor?

550
00:47:29,760 --> 00:47:33,320
See? She didn’t leave a single insult unsaid over a carpet.

551
00:47:34,840 --> 00:47:36,720
…such belittling, such humiliation…

552
00:47:40,880 --> 00:47:42,240
That's the way it is, dear.

553
00:47:42,360 --> 00:47:45,560
That's the difference between those above and those below.

554
00:47:45,760 --> 00:47:47,400
Their paths never meet.

555
00:47:49,840 --> 00:47:51,520
That’s how this world works.

556
00:47:54,440 --> 00:47:56,760
Come on. Don’t just stand there staring.

557
00:47:56,880 --> 00:48:01,240
There was a stain remover over there. Bring the cloth too, so we can wipe it.

558
00:48:17,560 --> 00:48:18,560
Yeah, yeah.

559
00:48:19,400 --> 00:48:21,440
It's important that it has a big garden.

560
00:48:21,520 --> 00:48:25,400
If it has an Olympic pool, even better.

561
00:48:26,160 --> 00:48:27,680
Just make sure it doesn’t lose

562
00:48:27,760 --> 00:48:30,480
its bohemian feel while adding modern elements.

563
00:48:30,560 --> 00:48:32,280
The woman I love is an architect.

564
00:48:32,840 --> 00:48:34,920
What matters most is that she likes it.

565
00:48:36,880 --> 00:48:38,040
That could work, sure.

566
00:48:38,960 --> 00:48:41,480
For example, pay special attention

567
00:48:41,800 --> 00:48:44,000
to the ones with wooden‑fenced gardens.

568
00:48:45,720 --> 00:48:48,040
We might even set up a small farm… exactly.

569
00:48:51,360 --> 00:48:53,640
Um…send me your portfolio.

570
00:48:54,320 --> 00:48:58,480
I’ll pick the ones I like and then we'll visit them together.

571
00:48:59,720 --> 00:49:00,640
Deal. Okay.

572
00:49:01,600 --> 00:49:03,400
I'll be waiting to hear from you.

573
00:49:21,240 --> 00:49:22,880
Come here a bit.

574
00:49:23,440 --> 00:49:25,080
Yes, Mr. Nezir?

575
00:49:25,840 --> 00:49:28,520
-How's it going, Burak? -Good. How about you?

576
00:49:28,960 --> 00:49:32,080
Good, nothing much. Same old, running around nonstop.

577
00:49:34,040 --> 00:49:35,120
Hey,

578
00:49:36,200 --> 00:49:38,480
What are you and Ateş plotting?

579
00:49:39,400 --> 00:49:41,640
I--nothing. We’re not plotting anything.

580
00:49:42,160 --> 00:49:45,360
Do you really think I’m buying that?

581
00:49:46,640 --> 00:49:47,680
You don’t?

582
00:49:47,920 --> 00:49:49,080
No, I don't.

583
00:49:52,840 --> 00:49:54,120
Listen, Burak.

584
00:49:54,640 --> 00:49:56,640
If you two are cooking something up…

585
00:49:56,720 --> 00:49:58,240
and you don’t tell me…

586
00:49:58,960 --> 00:50:01,800
and I find out on my own, it won’t be good for you.

587
00:50:04,520 --> 00:50:08,080
-Is that how it’s gonna be? -Yeah, that’s how it’s gonna be..

588
00:50:12,200 --> 00:50:14,280
Why are you staring at me like that?

589
00:50:15,240 --> 00:50:18,760
Everyone has their own way of spacing out.

590
00:50:20,200 --> 00:50:21,360
Is it hereditary?

591
00:50:22,280 --> 00:50:23,640
-No. -No?

592
00:50:25,360 --> 00:50:27,680
I pay attention to people with those traits.

593
00:50:27,760 --> 00:50:29,440
You're aware of this, right?

594
00:50:29,520 --> 00:50:30,680
I am.

595
00:50:31,080 --> 00:50:32,960
Well, you’re friends with my sister.

596
00:50:33,440 --> 00:50:37,320
And I care who my sister befriends.

597
00:50:38,520 --> 00:50:40,000
-Yes. -Yeah.

598
00:50:40,120 --> 00:50:41,360
Did I make myself clear?

599
00:50:41,680 --> 00:50:43,000
You did.

600
00:50:49,840 --> 00:50:52,400
Brother? What's going on?

601
00:50:53,720 --> 00:50:55,080
Don’t worry.

602
00:50:55,640 --> 00:50:57,520
Nothing much. We’re just talking.

603
00:50:58,120 --> 00:50:59,600
Yeah, we were talking.

604
00:50:59,680 --> 00:51:01,840
We were discussing the company’s outlook,

605
00:51:01,920 --> 00:51:04,880
where the economy and finances are headed.

606
00:51:04,960 --> 00:51:07,520
Yeah, Burak is very successful in this.

607
00:51:07,600 --> 00:51:09,040
-I appreciate him. -Thank you.

608
00:51:09,120 --> 00:51:12,440
-Wishing you continued success, brother. -Thank you. Thank you.

609
00:51:12,520 --> 00:51:13,520
Good job.

610
00:51:13,680 --> 00:51:16,320
Alright then, we’ll talk again.

611
00:51:16,480 --> 00:51:18,400
-See you later. -See you.

612
00:51:22,320 --> 00:51:25,400
-Are you alright, Burak? -I’m great. I’m perfect, apparently.

613
00:51:26,040 --> 00:51:28,720
-Thanks. -Fine. See you later, then.

614
00:51:28,800 --> 00:51:30,400
See you.

615
00:51:35,880 --> 00:51:38,480
Damn it, Nezir. That’s twice now.

616
00:51:38,560 --> 00:51:41,680
The third time… you’ll be eating dirt, Nezir.

617
00:51:44,040 --> 00:51:46,360
Anyway. I'll stay calm.

618
00:52:01,720 --> 00:52:03,760
I brought you some hot soup.

619
00:52:07,720 --> 00:52:09,080
Thank you, Çiçek.

620
00:52:17,200 --> 00:52:19,000
Wait, leave it to me.

621
00:52:20,320 --> 00:52:21,800
Let me--

622
00:52:23,160 --> 00:52:25,160
No, no. I can handle it myself.

623
00:52:27,560 --> 00:52:31,200
Oh no. I thought so too,

624
00:52:31,640 --> 00:52:33,200
but you’re still too weak.

625
00:52:33,560 --> 00:52:35,920
Don't burn yourself on top of everything.

626
00:52:49,320 --> 00:52:51,720
No matter how angry you say you are,

627
00:52:52,520 --> 00:52:54,000
you still love me.

628
00:52:58,400 --> 00:53:04,600
No one cares like this for someone they hate.

629
00:53:06,320 --> 00:53:08,400
I’m not angry at you, Malik.

630
00:53:09,040 --> 00:53:10,320
I’m hurt.

631
00:53:14,000 --> 00:53:16,080
I wish I were angry.

632
00:53:17,400 --> 00:53:20,000
That’s easier to fix.

633
00:53:36,960 --> 00:53:39,760
Those two shouldn’t be anywhere near each other.

634
00:53:40,240 --> 00:53:42,640
Let me go near him.

635
00:53:46,720 --> 00:53:49,640
Okay, did he finish his soup?

636
00:53:49,960 --> 00:53:50,920
Not yet.

637
00:53:51,000 --> 00:53:53,080
Let me get him to drink it quickly, dear.

638
00:53:53,200 --> 00:53:55,000
Step aside. Get up.

639
00:53:55,480 --> 00:53:57,520
Mom, why are you pushing me?

640
00:54:01,360 --> 00:54:03,200
Let's see.

641
00:54:03,280 --> 00:54:05,000
Come on, quick.

642
00:54:05,400 --> 00:54:07,880
Ohh, Let it heal you.

643
00:54:08,240 --> 00:54:10,760
May you get well soon.

644
00:54:11,720 --> 00:54:15,360
This will help you recover.

645
00:54:16,320 --> 00:54:18,080
Oh, with the help of God.

646
00:54:18,360 --> 00:54:21,080
Alright then. Enjoy, son.

647
00:54:24,280 --> 00:54:25,840
Thank you Binnaz aunt.

648
00:54:26,240 --> 00:54:27,680
The soup is delicious.

649
00:54:28,240 --> 00:54:30,240
Thanks. You’re okay now, right?

650
00:54:31,520 --> 00:54:32,760
Yes, I am.

651
00:54:34,600 --> 00:54:37,360
Good. Thank God. You’ll be up and about now.

652
00:54:38,400 --> 00:54:39,720
His fever’s down.

653
00:54:39,880 --> 00:54:40,960
You’ve bounced back.

654
00:54:42,360 --> 00:54:43,520
Let's check again.

655
00:54:44,640 --> 00:54:45,960
Ah, very good.

656
00:54:47,040 --> 00:54:48,360
35.5

657
00:54:48,560 --> 00:54:50,120
No, 36.5

658
00:54:50,400 --> 00:54:53,200
That’s normal. Very good.

659
00:55:00,440 --> 00:55:02,720
Put this away, dear. Come on now.

660
00:55:26,600 --> 00:55:28,360
Today was such a perfect day.

661
00:55:29,240 --> 00:55:32,200
Now and then, we’ll sneak away like this again, right?

662
00:55:37,840 --> 00:55:40,080
How am I supposed to tell you the truth…

663
00:55:40,360 --> 00:55:43,240
when you’re floating with happiness like this?

664
00:55:43,960 --> 00:55:45,880
You’ll shatter like glass…

665
00:55:46,600 --> 00:55:48,800
break into pieces. I know you will.

666
00:55:48,880 --> 00:55:50,840
I can’t stand the thought of it.

667
00:55:57,880 --> 00:56:00,600
But I can’t let you live inside a lie either.

668
00:56:01,360 --> 00:56:03,160
How long can I keep this from you?

669
00:56:03,920 --> 00:56:05,360
How long can I run from it?

670
00:56:08,080 --> 00:56:09,360
I love this necklace…

671
00:56:09,920 --> 00:56:11,160
it’s gorgeous.

672
00:56:20,960 --> 00:56:22,440
And it looks perfect on you.

673
00:56:26,160 --> 00:56:29,040
And we look perfect together, too.

674
00:56:31,160 --> 00:56:32,480
Ateş and Mercan…

675
00:56:33,920 --> 00:56:36,480
the inseparable ones.

676
00:56:39,680 --> 00:56:41,480
That’s what they’ll call us.

677
00:56:43,320 --> 00:56:46,600
Everywhere we go, people will stare.

678
00:56:46,800 --> 00:56:48,480
They’ll talk.

679
00:56:48,680 --> 00:56:50,920
Our names will always be said together.

680
00:56:52,880 --> 00:56:54,720
I don’t want anyone looking at you.

681
00:56:56,400 --> 00:56:57,720
It makes me jealous.

682
00:57:02,680 --> 00:57:05,040
You don’t need to be jealous. You know that.

683
00:57:06,840 --> 00:57:08,520
Try telling that to my heart.

684
00:57:09,760 --> 00:57:12,480
And what about the women who look at you?

685
00:57:13,880 --> 00:57:16,280
"Ateş, remember when we were in America…

686
00:57:16,360 --> 00:57:19,400
we watched movies, we ate this together. You remember?”

687
00:57:19,480 --> 00:57:21,120
"But Ateş…"

688
00:57:22,360 --> 00:57:24,600
Annoying liar.

689
00:57:25,560 --> 00:57:27,600
She made up all kinds of lies about you.

690
00:57:29,440 --> 00:57:31,800
Listen, you’re not seeing her again. I mean it.

691
00:57:33,040 --> 00:57:34,800
Alright, you already told me.

692
00:57:35,520 --> 00:57:38,280
Oh really? You agreed a little too fast.

693
00:57:39,480 --> 00:57:42,400
I’m not dumb enough to argue over something like that.

694
00:57:42,920 --> 00:57:44,560
If you say you won’t argue

695
00:57:44,640 --> 00:57:47,840
but still see her behind my back… that won’t end well.

696
00:57:48,320 --> 00:57:49,800
Mm Hmm.

697
00:57:54,080 --> 00:57:55,280
Agreed on that too.

698
00:57:56,400 --> 00:57:57,840
Agreed. On all of it.

699
00:58:09,280 --> 00:58:12,400
I totally forgot to send the project details.

700
00:58:14,720 --> 00:58:16,400
It slipped my mind completely.

701
00:58:17,080 --> 00:58:20,520
You’ve scrambled my brain. What can I do?

702
00:58:23,240 --> 00:58:24,640
I should go.

703
00:58:29,760 --> 00:58:31,080
Don’t.

704
00:58:33,200 --> 00:58:36,640
I have to. My boss will kill me.

705
00:58:37,840 --> 00:58:39,160
Hmm.

706
00:58:40,360 --> 00:58:42,120
Sounds like a cruel boss.

707
00:58:42,760 --> 00:58:44,160
Very cruel.

708
00:59:10,840 --> 00:59:12,560
How long can I hide this?

709
00:59:13,400 --> 00:59:15,000
How long can I run from it?

710
00:59:26,200 --> 00:59:28,120
What’s wrong, Mom? You look worried.

711
00:59:28,320 --> 00:59:29,680
Did something happen?

712
00:59:30,880 --> 00:59:33,200
Sit with me, sweetheart. Let’s talk for a bit.

713
00:59:34,040 --> 00:59:34,960
Okay.

714
00:59:38,800 --> 00:59:40,160
So, what is it?

715
00:59:41,120 --> 00:59:43,520
I saw you taking care of Malik.

716
00:59:45,200 --> 00:59:47,480
You were upset when he got sick, weren’t you?

717
00:59:50,760 --> 00:59:53,120
That’s what love is.

718
00:59:53,320 --> 00:59:59,080
When the person you love is hurting, your whole world falls apart.

719
01:00:01,600 --> 01:00:04,720
I was upset, mom. I won’t lie.

720
01:00:08,280 --> 01:00:10,200
Malik is a good boy.

721
01:00:10,400 --> 01:00:11,920
He loves you, too.

722
01:00:14,080 --> 01:00:19,120
But he’s not the Malik we knew anymore.

723
01:00:22,480 --> 01:00:24,440
He’s the son of a rich family now.

724
01:00:28,840 --> 01:00:31,560
And you’ll say, "But he’s working here as a driver."

725
01:00:32,600 --> 01:00:34,520
That doesn’t change a thing.

726
01:00:40,480 --> 01:00:45,280
That mansion… he's like one of those who live there.

727
01:00:46,720 --> 01:00:50,200
Two different worlds in the same courtyard.

728
01:00:50,920 --> 01:00:52,960
There’s them… and there’s us.

729
01:00:56,200 --> 01:00:58,520
They own everything.

730
01:00:59,280 --> 01:01:00,680
We serve them.

731
01:01:09,040 --> 01:01:11,440
If we ever leave this roof,

732
01:01:11,800 --> 01:01:15,760
we have nowhere to go… no work, nothing.

733
01:01:19,920 --> 01:01:21,960
They’ll never understand our lives.

734
01:01:22,320 --> 01:01:23,840
Malik won’t either.

735
01:01:29,000 --> 01:01:30,520
So, the long story short,

736
01:01:31,920 --> 01:01:35,960
Even if you marry him,

737
01:01:37,720 --> 01:01:40,960
you’ll never escape being "the servant girl Çiçek."

738
01:01:48,480 --> 01:01:51,040
That label will follow you everywhere.

739
01:01:58,360 --> 01:02:01,280
His… family…

740
01:02:02,120 --> 01:02:04,880
they’ll look down on you. They’ll crush you.

741
01:02:10,040 --> 01:02:14,360
There’s a wall between you now--

742
01:02:22,000 --> 01:02:28,440
one you can only cross with courage and a very strong heart.

743
01:02:32,880 --> 01:02:34,880
Can you handle that?

744
01:02:35,960 --> 01:02:38,760
That’s what you need to ask yourself, dear.

745
01:03:31,560 --> 01:03:34,000
I didn't say you could come in.

746
01:03:34,280 --> 01:03:35,960
And you didn’t say I couldn’t.

747
01:03:37,440 --> 01:03:39,360
Could you leave?

748
01:03:39,880 --> 01:03:41,800
I’m working. You’re distracting me.

749
01:03:45,000 --> 01:03:46,280
You’re such a fool.

750
01:03:47,080 --> 01:03:48,880
Actually, you’re an idiot.

751
01:03:51,840 --> 01:03:53,760
I thought you were smarter than this.

752
01:03:57,280 --> 01:03:58,560
I was wrong.

753
01:04:03,440 --> 01:04:06,080
If you’re done insulting me, you can go.

754
01:04:06,720 --> 01:04:08,040
These aren’t insults.

755
01:04:08,320 --> 01:04:09,960
They’re facts.

756
01:04:13,320 --> 01:04:15,880
For instance, how well do you even know Ateş?

757
01:04:18,480 --> 01:04:20,320
Not well enough, right?

758
01:04:24,760 --> 01:04:27,240
Yet you two wander around like lovebirds.

759
01:04:31,400 --> 01:04:33,440
Have you ever wondered who he really is?

760
01:04:38,320 --> 01:04:40,560
He showed up out of nowhere.

761
01:04:41,800 --> 01:04:43,600
Took over your company.

762
01:04:46,120 --> 01:04:49,360
Then demanded a 187-day marriage.

763
01:04:53,200 --> 01:04:55,040
One hundred and eighty‑seven days!

764
01:04:59,600 --> 01:05:01,240
You signed. You married him.

765
01:05:02,680 --> 01:05:04,680
And after that,

766
01:05:05,520 --> 01:05:11,280
he tortured you and your family in every way possible.

767
01:05:15,280 --> 01:05:21,000
Yet you fell in love with him without asking a single "why."

768
01:05:24,600 --> 01:05:26,760
Isn’t that stupid?

769
01:05:30,160 --> 01:05:32,280
Fine, let’s say I’m stupid.

770
01:05:32,360 --> 01:05:33,760
It was my choice.

771
01:05:34,760 --> 01:05:36,240
What’s it to you?

772
01:05:36,880 --> 01:05:38,440
What are you after?

773
01:05:39,200 --> 01:05:41,000
What do you want from me?

774
01:05:41,680 --> 01:05:44,760
You’re mean, you’re jealous, fine.

775
01:05:45,480 --> 01:05:47,560
But that’s not enough.

776
01:05:47,680 --> 01:05:49,440
There must be something else.

777
01:05:49,760 --> 01:05:51,360
Tell me. What am I missing?

778
01:05:52,800 --> 01:05:55,160
There’s so much you don’t know.

779
01:05:56,080 --> 01:05:58,640
I don’t even know where to begin.

780
01:06:01,040 --> 01:06:02,880
But I don’t have time to explain.

781
01:06:02,960 --> 01:06:04,080
Hm.

782
01:06:04,800 --> 01:06:07,040
If you know Ateş even a little,

783
01:06:07,520 --> 01:06:11,120
you should know he never does anything without a reason.

784
01:06:14,720 --> 01:06:16,760
Didn’t you ever wonder why 187 days?

785
01:06:17,560 --> 01:06:19,760
Did it never cross your mind to ask him?

786
01:06:21,880 --> 01:06:23,520
Of course it did.

787
01:06:28,080 --> 01:06:29,600
Did you get an answer?

788
01:07:00,440 --> 01:07:02,760
Go on, Ateş.

789
01:07:02,840 --> 01:07:05,000
Go see the wreck your loved one has become.

790
01:07:07,840 --> 01:07:10,400
I’m going to shatter your happiness into pieces.

791
01:07:11,680 --> 01:07:13,920
And then I’ll be the one comforting you.

792
01:07:33,160 --> 01:07:34,600
I missed you.

793
01:07:36,360 --> 01:07:37,440
That was fast.

794
01:07:48,440 --> 01:07:49,680
Ateş…

795
01:07:51,200 --> 01:07:52,400
Yes?

796
01:07:56,800 --> 01:07:59,000
There’s something I’m curious about.

797
01:08:01,480 --> 01:08:02,480
What is it?

798
01:08:07,160 --> 01:08:09,120
I… want to ask you something.

799
01:08:12,640 --> 01:08:15,240
What’s wrong, Mercan? Is something bothering you?

800
01:08:15,560 --> 01:08:19,120
Um… I want to ask you about…

801
01:08:21,000 --> 01:08:22,600
187.

802
01:08:29,840 --> 01:08:32,560
What does it mean?

803
01:08:39,200 --> 01:08:42,120
Why did you want a 187-day marriage with me?

804
01:09:44,120 --> 01:09:46,840
Come on. Just an answer, please.

805
01:10:11,280 --> 01:10:12,360
Sit down.

806
01:10:16,880 --> 01:10:19,000
It’s time we talked about this.

807
01:10:23,520 --> 01:10:25,000
You mean so much to me.

808
01:10:28,840 --> 01:10:30,760
More than you can imagine…

809
01:10:38,360 --> 01:10:40,600
That’s why I’m going to tell you everything…

810
01:10:40,680 --> 01:10:42,360
…no hiding, no holding back.

811
01:10:48,400 --> 01:10:51,440
After you hear this, you might want to walk out of my life.

812
01:10:57,320 --> 01:10:58,640
You might even hate me.

813
01:11:05,520 --> 01:11:07,480
But I love you so much

814
01:11:09,800 --> 01:11:11,840
that I have to risk losing you.

815
01:11:20,240 --> 01:11:22,800
I don’t want a single lie between us anymore.

816
01:11:32,440 --> 01:11:36,920
I came here-- Don’t. Don’t say anything.

817
01:11:39,360 --> 01:11:41,000
Whatever you’re about to tell me…

818
01:11:42,720 --> 01:11:44,440
it could ruin us, couldn’t it?

819
01:11:49,760 --> 01:11:53,000
It could even… break us apart?

820
01:11:56,720 --> 01:11:58,760
I’m not ready for that…

821
01:12:00,040 --> 01:12:02,720
I don’t want to lose you, Ateş.

822
01:12:04,760 --> 01:12:06,360
For the first time in so long,

823
01:12:06,520 --> 01:12:09,080
I remembered what it feels like to be happy.

824
01:12:12,080 --> 01:12:13,920
Not when I just got you back.

825
01:12:15,760 --> 01:12:18,320
No. Not now.

826
01:12:21,160 --> 01:12:22,720
But you need to know the truth.

827
01:12:22,840 --> 01:12:24,280
I said I don’t want to.

828
01:12:24,520 --> 01:12:26,400
You have the right to know everything.

829
01:12:28,840 --> 01:12:30,760
Whatever the cost, I have to tell you.

830
01:12:31,480 --> 01:12:32,320
No, you don’t.

831
01:12:33,480 --> 01:12:36,880
Listen, we have so much work today. Let’s finish that first.

832
01:12:37,760 --> 01:12:39,080
I’m going now.

833
01:12:39,280 --> 01:12:40,440
We--

834
01:12:41,280 --> 01:12:42,480
I don’t want to hear it!

835
01:13:05,440 --> 01:13:07,120
If only running from the truth…

836
01:13:10,840 --> 01:13:12,280
were that easy…

837
01:13:29,280 --> 01:13:31,680
It’s been this way since forever, dear.

838
01:13:33,640 --> 01:13:36,960
They’re one world, we’re another.

839
01:13:37,880 --> 01:13:39,640
They don’t understand our language,

840
01:13:40,440 --> 01:13:42,680
and we don’t understand theirs.

841
01:13:46,000 --> 01:13:47,080
But Mom--

842
01:13:48,720 --> 01:13:50,520
You see the Haydar family.

843
01:13:52,480 --> 01:13:54,320
What have we ever gotten from them?

844
01:13:55,200 --> 01:13:57,640
Humiliation, disrespect…

845
01:14:04,080 --> 01:14:05,520
Everything changes,

846
01:14:05,840 --> 01:14:10,240
but the rich‑poor divide never does, dear.

847
01:14:12,160 --> 01:14:13,200
…never changes.

848
01:14:17,560 --> 01:14:19,160
Meaning…

849
01:14:19,240 --> 01:14:23,840
To his family, you’ll always be

850
01:14:23,960 --> 01:14:26,440
"the servant girl Çiçek."

851
01:14:30,520 --> 01:14:32,880
One day, your love will tire.

852
01:14:33,600 --> 01:14:39,080
Maybe even Malik will start seeing you as less than him.

853
01:14:46,440 --> 01:14:49,520
Can you carry something like that?

854
01:15:11,000 --> 01:15:13,560
My love will never fade, Binnaz aunt!

855
01:15:17,120 --> 01:15:18,040
You’re right,

856
01:15:19,000 --> 01:15:21,920
the rich and poor have always existed…

857
01:15:24,680 --> 01:15:28,680
Yes, but love also has existed since the world began.

858
01:15:38,240 --> 01:15:43,000
And love is the strongest, most beautiful thing in this world.

859
01:15:44,640 --> 01:15:46,480
I hid who I was because I was afraid

860
01:15:46,920 --> 01:15:49,560
Çiçek would think like you and pull away from me.

861
01:15:53,560 --> 01:15:55,360
I won’t let anyone hurt her.

862
01:16:03,440 --> 01:16:08,680
Her happiness is worth more than money, more than anything.

863
01:16:19,560 --> 01:16:21,040
When you’re truly in love,

864
01:16:22,440 --> 01:16:25,440
you know your real wealth is the heart of the one you love.

865
01:16:29,000 --> 01:16:32,480
Compared to Çiçek’s heart, my family’s money means nothing.

866
01:16:40,080 --> 01:16:44,320
Çiçek is my whole fortune,

867
01:16:47,120 --> 01:16:48,200
my everything.

868
01:17:28,760 --> 01:17:32,080
After you hear this, you might want to walk out of my life.

869
01:17:32,560 --> 01:17:34,000
You might hate me.

870
01:17:35,520 --> 01:17:37,440
But I love you so much

871
01:17:39,760 --> 01:17:41,760
that I have to risk losing you.

872
01:17:44,360 --> 01:17:46,920
I don’t want a single lie between us anymore.

873
01:17:51,960 --> 01:17:55,560
No… no, it can’t be.

874
01:17:56,080 --> 01:17:57,560
I can’t hate Ateş!

875
01:17:58,600 --> 01:18:01,080
I can’t bear losing him!

876
01:18:04,680 --> 01:18:07,760
No…no.

877
01:18:20,160 --> 01:18:21,200
Mercan!

878
01:18:25,160 --> 01:18:26,680
Mercan.

879
01:18:28,760 --> 01:18:31,480
Whatever happens, we need the truth, Mercan.

880
01:18:31,720 --> 01:18:35,800
MERCAN: No… I don’t need the truth. I need you!

881
01:18:41,920 --> 01:18:45,080
Look, let’s make a deal.

882
01:18:47,200 --> 01:18:52,280
I… Until I ask you to tell me, let's forget it.

883
01:18:54,560 --> 01:18:57,600
Pretend I never asked. And don’t ever bring it up again.

884
01:19:10,560 --> 01:19:12,720
What’s wrong, Ateş?

885
01:19:14,800 --> 01:19:16,520
I want to tell Mercan everything.

886
01:19:18,000 --> 01:19:19,560
But now she’s the one running.

887
01:19:20,000 --> 01:19:21,480
She doesn’t want to hear me.

888
01:19:24,080 --> 01:19:25,360
Then don’t tell her, Ateş…

889
01:19:27,320 --> 01:19:31,480
Just because a medicine is strong doesn’t mean it’s right for every wound.

890
01:19:33,080 --> 01:19:34,880
We’re reaching the end of the road.

891
01:19:37,480 --> 01:19:40,960
I know her. Mercan can’t turn her back on the truth.

892
01:19:43,680 --> 01:19:45,920
And I can’t carry this burden any longer.

893
01:19:48,720 --> 01:19:52,640
The real test starts now. For both of you.

894
01:19:55,360 --> 01:19:57,560
There’s no test I wouldn’t face for Mercan.

895
01:20:20,440 --> 01:20:22,480
Done!

896
01:20:24,360 --> 01:20:25,520
My shift’s over.

897
01:20:26,960 --> 01:20:27,880
Whew.

898
01:20:28,600 --> 01:20:29,800
It was a long day.

899
01:20:32,160 --> 01:20:34,360
At least finish what you started.

900
01:20:37,400 --> 01:20:40,160
Work never ends, Ms. Zahide.

901
01:20:40,440 --> 01:20:44,720
If I finish what’s in one hand, the other hand gets jealous.

902
01:20:44,800 --> 01:20:47,920
Okay, whatever. I really can’t deal with you right now.

903
01:20:51,120 --> 01:20:53,160
Come on, pack up so we can finally leave.

904
01:20:53,240 --> 01:20:54,320
Are you going out?

905
01:20:54,760 --> 01:20:57,200
No, we’re gonna sleep here and keep working

906
01:20:57,280 --> 01:20:59,400
so you can get even richer, golden boy.

907
01:21:05,640 --> 01:21:07,240
Want to grab dinner after work?

908
01:21:07,320 --> 01:21:10,600
Thanks, but I’ll pass. I’ve got things to do. I'm a busy person.

909
01:21:10,680 --> 01:21:11,720
You?

910
01:21:12,120 --> 01:21:13,000
I have work to do.

911
01:21:13,480 --> 01:21:15,760
Also, you’re the boss’s kid.

912
01:21:15,920 --> 01:21:18,880
Don’t hang out with people like us. You’ll lose your shine.

913
01:21:19,120 --> 01:21:22,360
Don’t say that, bro. It’s not like that.

914
01:21:22,720 --> 01:21:24,760
As if what we think matters, Burak.

915
01:21:26,960 --> 01:21:29,520
Alright. Do whatever you want. I’m out.

916
01:21:32,320 --> 01:21:35,960
Hey, come on. Don’t be so hard on him.

917
01:21:36,320 --> 01:21:40,960
The kid got rich overnight. God, look at me too. I want to be rich.

918
01:21:41,120 --> 01:21:43,360
I'm a good kid. I want to be rich.

919
01:21:43,920 --> 01:21:46,760
Come on Ms. Zahide. You don't get rich by working.

920
01:21:46,840 --> 01:21:50,280
You’re jinxing him. Seriously, stop. You’ll give him the evil eye.

921
01:21:50,360 --> 01:21:52,480
Wait. I'll grab my purse from downstairs.

922
01:21:52,600 --> 01:21:54,680
You talk like being rich is a bad thing.

923
01:21:54,760 --> 01:21:55,760
It’s a good thing!

924
01:21:55,880 --> 01:21:57,320
But you need luck. Like him.

925
01:22:43,000 --> 01:22:44,400
I don’t know what to do.

926
01:22:50,920 --> 01:22:56,360
My heart is clear… but my head is a mess.

927
01:23:00,760 --> 01:23:03,360
If you want to talk about the truth, I’m right here.

928
01:23:09,680 --> 01:23:13,400
It got dusty… I was just…

929
01:23:14,120 --> 01:23:15,840
You barely ate at the dinner table.

930
01:23:18,240 --> 01:23:20,000
I brought you something.

931
01:23:44,160 --> 01:23:46,400
Is it warm in here?

932
01:23:48,080 --> 01:23:49,840
The weather’s cold though, right?

933
01:23:50,680 --> 01:23:52,640
Maybe it’s global warming or something.

934
01:23:52,760 --> 01:23:55,440
Seasons are all… messed up. It’s weird.

935
01:23:57,440 --> 01:23:58,480
Mercan…

936
01:24:00,200 --> 01:24:03,440
Here, before it gets cold, take a bite of this… go on.

937
01:24:08,400 --> 01:24:09,600
-Mercan-- -Shh!

938
01:24:10,200 --> 01:24:11,800
Don’t talk with your mouth full.

939
01:24:13,240 --> 01:24:14,360
Okay, I'll slow down.

940
01:24:14,640 --> 01:24:17,360
That’s better. Eat. Let’s just enjoy ourselves a bit.

941
01:24:24,120 --> 01:24:25,480
It's delicious.

942
01:24:34,320 --> 01:24:35,560
Let’s get a house.

943
01:24:38,840 --> 01:24:40,160
Just ours.

944
01:24:43,080 --> 01:24:44,360
That would be great.

945
01:24:47,040 --> 01:24:48,560
Could we really get one?

946
01:24:49,920 --> 01:24:52,080
I mean, can we move out of here?

947
01:24:54,400 --> 01:24:55,600
If that’s what you want.

948
01:24:58,000 --> 01:25:00,920
Yes, that's what I want.

949
01:25:05,560 --> 01:25:06,680
Just the two of us.

950
01:25:08,080 --> 01:25:09,600
A house that’s ours.

951
01:25:10,720 --> 01:25:12,280
No one else inside…

952
01:25:13,760 --> 01:25:15,320
A world that’s ours.

953
01:25:16,160 --> 01:25:17,640
Wouldn’t that be beautiful?

954
01:25:20,240 --> 01:25:21,280
I’ll decorate it.

955
01:25:21,840 --> 01:25:23,160
Our taste together.

956
01:25:23,720 --> 01:25:25,040
Leave some work for me too.

957
01:25:26,000 --> 01:25:26,880
Okay. Fine.

958
01:25:28,680 --> 01:25:30,080
May be close to the company?

959
01:25:30,600 --> 01:25:32,080
Easy commute.

960
01:25:32,760 --> 01:25:35,280
I’d like it to be somewhere in nature…

961
01:25:35,840 --> 01:25:36,920
away from the city.

962
01:25:44,600 --> 01:25:45,640
Ateş?

963
01:25:46,760 --> 01:25:47,560
Yes?

964
01:25:50,600 --> 01:25:51,960
You love me, right?

965
01:25:59,640 --> 01:26:01,000
You know I do.

966
01:26:22,800 --> 01:26:24,600
Come on, you haven't eaten anything.

967
01:26:25,360 --> 01:26:26,520
These will be finished.

968
01:26:27,800 --> 01:26:29,080
Open your mouth.

969
01:26:50,400 --> 01:26:53,040
Neclas are staying in Tuscany for a month.

970
01:26:55,280 --> 01:26:58,520
I told her, "You’ll get bored, go to Sicily."

971
01:27:01,520 --> 01:27:03,240
You’re dragging this out too long…

972
01:27:04,840 --> 01:27:06,440
You act like you’re the victim.

973
01:27:07,120 --> 01:27:12,280
I’m trying to talk, but it’s pointless.

974
01:27:14,080 --> 01:27:17,080
The more I try, the more arrogant you get.

975
01:27:20,680 --> 01:27:23,760
You made yourself the guilty one with what you did, Nermin.

976
01:27:26,520 --> 01:27:29,960
What I did? Wow.

977
01:27:30,600 --> 01:27:31,400
Wow.

978
01:27:32,080 --> 01:27:34,760
You’re the reason things got this far.

979
01:27:35,240 --> 01:27:39,280
Sure, everything’s my fault.

980
01:27:40,120 --> 01:27:41,040
How convenient.

981
01:27:41,840 --> 01:27:46,520
You stir everything up, have kids with other women…

982
01:27:47,240 --> 01:27:49,080
and I’m the guilty one.

983
01:27:50,560 --> 01:27:52,760
It’s just dirt on your hands, right?

984
01:27:52,920 --> 01:27:54,520
You wash them and it’s all gone.

985
01:27:54,640 --> 01:27:56,280
Watch your mouth, Nermin.

986
01:27:57,040 --> 01:28:01,920
Listen, Haydar. Nurgül was a stain on our lives.

987
01:28:04,120 --> 01:28:06,440
Everything I did was to protect my family.

988
01:28:06,760 --> 01:28:08,200
And I’d do it again.

989
01:28:10,440 --> 01:28:12,520
Family, huh.

990
01:28:14,680 --> 01:28:17,280
As if we don’t know what you were really protecting.

991
01:28:17,800 --> 01:28:19,320
And you, Haydar?

992
01:28:19,880 --> 01:28:21,640
What have you ever protected?

993
01:29:08,680 --> 01:29:12,320
After you hear this, you might want to walk out of my life.

994
01:29:16,560 --> 01:29:18,080
You might even hate me.

995
01:29:21,320 --> 01:29:23,440
But I love you so much

996
01:29:25,560 --> 01:29:27,640
that I have to risk losing you.

997
01:29:33,280 --> 01:29:35,960
I don’t want a single lie between us anymore.

998
01:29:52,760 --> 01:29:56,120
If I take one more hit, I won’t be able to get back up.

999
01:29:57,560 --> 01:29:59,240
But even with all this bad luck…

1000
01:30:00,400 --> 01:30:02,040
in a way, I’m just as lucky.

1001
01:30:05,000 --> 01:30:06,360
Because I have you.

1002
01:30:07,480 --> 01:30:08,600
Because you’re mine.

1003
01:30:09,720 --> 01:30:11,000
Because I have your love…

1004
01:30:14,040 --> 01:30:16,280
You’re the only thing I’m holding on to, Ateş.

1005
01:30:17,320 --> 01:30:18,680
I trust you completely.

1006
01:30:19,920 --> 01:30:22,760
And I know you’d never lie to me.

1007
01:30:25,960 --> 01:30:27,600
Did you sleep?

1008
01:30:30,040 --> 01:30:31,480
Yes, I did…

1009
01:30:32,720 --> 01:30:35,680
When will you get up?

1010
01:30:38,080 --> 01:30:39,640
I don’t think I want to.

1011
01:30:42,000 --> 01:30:43,800
I’m in the deepest part of my sleep.

1012
01:30:46,120 --> 01:30:47,440
Okay.

1013
01:30:49,520 --> 01:30:51,600
It’d be nice to stay here for a while.

1014
01:30:54,840 --> 01:30:56,640
We could meet in my dreams and talk.

1015
01:30:57,680 --> 01:30:58,920
I’d miss you though.

1016
01:31:00,240 --> 01:31:02,080
I said we’d meet in my dreams.

1017
01:31:06,600 --> 01:31:07,720
Mercan…

1018
01:31:20,120 --> 01:31:21,560
You love me. Right?

1019
01:31:30,120 --> 01:31:32,160
So much…

1020
01:31:37,320 --> 01:31:38,800
That’s what matters.

1021
01:31:42,680 --> 01:31:44,520
That’s the only thing I need to know.

1022
01:31:47,280 --> 01:31:48,520
I love you too.

1023
01:32:23,280 --> 01:32:25,280
God, help me.

1024
01:32:25,480 --> 01:32:28,840
(inhale) Show me a way out.

1025
01:32:35,640 --> 01:32:37,440
I won’t let anyone hurt Çiçek.

1026
01:32:39,000 --> 01:32:44,560
Her happiness is worth more than money or anything else.

1027
01:32:46,960 --> 01:32:48,560
When someone is truly in love,

1028
01:32:49,840 --> 01:32:52,960
they know their real wealth is the heart of the one they love.

1029
01:32:55,040 --> 01:32:58,760
Compared to Çiçek’s heart, my family’s money is nothing.

1030
01:33:04,960 --> 01:33:08,120
I love you so much but…

1031
01:33:08,240 --> 01:33:12,480
I have so many "buts"…

1032
01:33:18,960 --> 01:33:20,640
Because I love you so much.

1033
01:33:21,520 --> 01:33:24,800
I came all the way from Egypt… for you.

1034
01:33:25,320 --> 01:33:26,840
So you’d be my Çiçek…

1035
01:33:33,160 --> 01:33:34,840
You became the flower of my heart.

1036
01:33:35,760 --> 01:33:38,960
Will you be the flower of my home too?

1037
01:33:39,480 --> 01:33:40,800
Çiçek…

1038
01:33:45,480 --> 01:33:46,800
Will you marry me?

1039
01:33:58,640 --> 01:34:02,320
Yes! I will! Yes to all of it! Yes yes yes!

1040
01:34:32,200 --> 01:34:34,240
I don’t want a life without you.

1041
01:35:25,640 --> 01:35:27,000
Mercan.

1042
01:35:38,600 --> 01:35:39,520
Mercan?

1043
01:35:41,480 --> 01:35:42,360
I'm here.

1044
01:35:47,640 --> 01:35:48,520
Good morning.

1045
01:35:50,000 --> 01:35:50,960
Good morning.

1046
01:35:52,880 --> 01:35:54,720
When I didn’t see you… I got worried.

1047
01:35:57,160 --> 01:36:00,080
I woke up early. Couldn’t sleep much.

1048
01:36:04,640 --> 01:36:06,800
Burak’s coming, I guess I got excited.

1049
01:36:11,080 --> 01:36:13,160
You can come in. I’m almost done.

1050
01:36:21,240 --> 01:36:22,760
Why were you worried about me?

1051
01:36:23,640 --> 01:36:24,720
It’s really early.

1052
01:36:25,440 --> 01:36:27,240
When I didn’t see you… I don’t know…

1053
01:36:28,520 --> 01:36:29,800
Were you scared I left?

1054
01:36:31,200 --> 01:36:33,040
I won’t let you leave, you know that.

1055
01:36:34,200 --> 01:36:35,680
Why would I leave anyway?

1056
01:36:40,720 --> 01:36:41,920
Not before I do this.

1057
01:36:42,040 --> 01:36:44,520
Starting a war again, huh?

1058
01:36:44,680 --> 01:36:47,640
You lost when we washed the car, and you’ll lose again.

1059
01:36:47,720 --> 01:36:51,600
I didn’t lose that one and I won’t lose this one.

1060
01:36:58,160 --> 01:36:59,840
I don’t enter battles I can’t win.

1061
01:37:00,560 --> 01:37:03,080
What a coincidence, neither do I. I always play big.

1062
01:37:03,560 --> 01:37:05,480
Come here, you.

1063
01:37:05,600 --> 01:37:08,760
Don’t you dare.

1064
01:37:11,120 --> 01:37:14,080
There you go. Here's the war you wanted. Oh, no!

1065
01:37:14,200 --> 01:37:15,320
You want war? No!

1066
01:37:17,800 --> 01:37:23,240
You shouldn’t have started this war.

1067
01:37:23,320 --> 01:37:26,400
Okay. Stop that. I’m soaked. Okay.

1068
01:37:26,480 --> 01:37:27,920
Say you give up.

1069
01:37:28,000 --> 01:37:32,200
I give up, okay. Okay. I give up.

1070
01:37:44,480 --> 01:37:48,480
I’m soaked everywhere. If I get sick, I’ll blame you.

1071
01:37:48,560 --> 01:37:50,440
You know, I wouldn't let you get sick?

1072
01:37:53,440 --> 01:37:55,120
Go take a shower and change.

1073
01:37:55,840 --> 01:37:58,040
-I don’t want you getting sick, okay? -Okay.

1074
01:37:59,720 --> 01:38:02,000
I'll be waiting for you in the room.

1075
01:38:19,720 --> 01:38:20,920
Ateş?

1076
01:38:25,400 --> 01:38:26,360
Ateş?

1077
01:38:42,040 --> 01:38:44,680
Haven't you left already?

1078
01:38:48,000 --> 01:38:49,200
Not yet.

1079
01:39:29,280 --> 01:39:31,560
I'll get in the bathroom

1080
01:39:31,880 --> 01:39:33,160
and you get changed.

1081
01:39:33,800 --> 01:39:36,480
Okay, I will.

1082
01:39:37,360 --> 01:39:38,520
You look so cute.

1083
01:39:41,360 --> 01:39:42,600
Thanks.

1084
01:40:12,360 --> 01:40:15,640
Berat, stop. What are you doing?

1085
01:40:15,840 --> 01:40:17,880
Zehra, I can’t help it!! What can I do?

1086
01:40:18,040 --> 01:40:19,640
I’m so happy, Berat!

1087
01:40:19,720 --> 01:40:22,400
Even if it’s in secret, we’re finally getting married…

1088
01:40:22,480 --> 01:40:25,000
Honestly, I’m bursting with excitement too, Zehra!

1089
01:40:25,080 --> 01:40:26,080
I feel like dancing.

1090
01:40:27,840 --> 01:40:30,040
Shh, after the wedding…

1091
01:40:31,040 --> 01:40:35,240
Yes, you're right but let’s not get caught on the way to the ceremony.

1092
01:40:35,320 --> 01:40:37,760
Oh, God forbid. That would be a disaster!

1093
01:40:37,840 --> 01:40:39,800
Right. Then you know what we should do?

1094
01:40:39,880 --> 01:40:40,720
What?

1095
01:40:40,800 --> 01:40:41,960
We’ll leave separately.

1096
01:40:42,800 --> 01:40:46,040
Let's leave separately. and meet at the wedding hall. Okay?

1097
01:40:46,160 --> 01:40:49,240
You’re right. We’re so close. Let’s not crash into a wall now.

1098
01:40:49,320 --> 01:40:51,240
God forbid!

1099
01:40:51,360 --> 01:40:52,520
Good luck.

1100
01:40:52,680 --> 01:40:53,600
-Good luck. -Okay.

1101
01:40:53,720 --> 01:40:55,000
-So, I’m gonna head out now. -Yeah.

1102
01:40:55,080 --> 01:40:58,480
I'll get ready and slip out, We'll change in the bridal room.

1103
01:40:59,520 --> 01:41:01,280
So smart. So sensible.

1104
01:41:01,840 --> 01:41:03,240
I love this.

1105
01:41:03,320 --> 01:41:05,440
-Alright, see you then. -See you.

1106
01:41:06,000 --> 01:41:07,920
-Don't get caught. -Oh no, you too.

1107
01:41:08,240 --> 01:41:09,520
Go before anyone sees you.

1108
01:41:20,080 --> 01:41:22,080
Oh God… you, Berat…

1109
01:41:23,680 --> 01:41:25,240
Berat!

1110
01:41:29,400 --> 01:41:30,680
Oh— Mom!

1111
01:41:36,840 --> 01:41:39,600
Mom, what’s up? Give me a kiss, sweetheart.

1112
01:41:40,720 --> 01:41:42,720
-Oh. -Good grief.

1113
01:41:43,280 --> 01:41:45,440
What is it son? Are you alright?

1114
01:41:46,280 --> 01:41:49,080
Have you lost your mind? What are you dancing for?

1115
01:41:49,280 --> 01:41:53,000
Son, we were together two minutes ago. I’m fine, I’m fine.

1116
01:41:53,080 --> 01:41:55,320
I don’t know… it’s a busy mansion.

1117
01:41:55,400 --> 01:41:58,280
Anything can happen anytime. Things change fast, you know.

1118
01:41:59,040 --> 01:42:00,000
So, that's why…

1119
01:42:00,400 --> 01:42:01,240
Good grief… son?

1120
01:42:01,320 --> 01:42:03,680
You started your day more hyper than the mansion.

1121
01:42:03,760 --> 01:42:05,360
Dancing around, huh?

1122
01:42:06,120 --> 01:42:08,800
I barely have a brain left and don't take that too!

1123
01:42:09,360 --> 01:42:11,120
I’m fine, I’m fine. Thanks.

1124
01:42:11,400 --> 01:42:12,680
How about you?

1125
01:42:12,760 --> 01:42:16,480
Good… good, Mom. We’re getting by. You know…

1126
01:42:16,840 --> 01:42:18,480
Good then.

1127
01:42:19,000 --> 01:42:20,680
Oh, I just remembered.

1128
01:42:20,760 --> 01:42:25,160
There’s old stuff piled up in the back, I need to clean it.

1129
01:42:25,320 --> 01:42:27,960
-Alright, Mom? Kisses. -Stop. Stop. Stop!

1130
01:42:28,600 --> 01:42:31,400
Forget the old junk in the back.

1131
01:42:31,480 --> 01:42:37,400
I need you today. There are things to buy, things to pick up, things to carry.

1132
01:42:37,840 --> 01:42:38,880
Today?! Yeah.

1133
01:42:39,040 --> 01:42:41,000
-Not today… -Why not?

1134
01:42:42,120 --> 01:42:43,080
Ugh!

1135
01:42:44,680 --> 01:42:47,800
Today… today my back started hurting a bit, Mom!

1136
01:42:48,600 --> 01:42:49,920
It’s shooting down my leg.

1137
01:42:50,240 --> 01:42:53,280
I don’t know, maybe it came on suddenly, maybe a draft hit me…

1138
01:42:53,480 --> 01:42:56,000
I should go. Right?

1139
01:42:56,280 --> 01:42:58,120
You were dancing two minutes ago, son.

1140
01:42:58,200 --> 01:42:59,920
You're now standing like a stick right in front of me.

1141
01:43:00,000 --> 01:43:02,280
What happened just now for a draft to hit you?

1142
01:43:02,360 --> 01:43:03,800
It just came suddenly, Mom.

1143
01:43:03,920 --> 01:43:06,640
It just happened. You know how it hits all of a sudden…

1144
01:43:06,720 --> 01:43:09,400
That’s why. And I’ve got things to do outside anyway.

1145
01:43:09,480 --> 01:43:11,480
I’ll get it done even in this condition.

1146
01:43:12,040 --> 01:43:13,160
Um, wait, wait. Wait.

1147
01:43:13,560 --> 01:43:14,560
No, you can't.

1148
01:43:14,640 --> 01:43:16,560
I told you I need you, son.

1149
01:43:16,960 --> 01:43:18,280
Move! Move!

1150
01:43:20,640 --> 01:43:23,320
Son! Don't drive me crazy. Move!

1151
01:43:24,080 --> 01:43:25,200
Come on!

1152
01:43:26,200 --> 01:43:29,240
Let’s go… dance if you want! Good grief!

1153
01:43:31,680 --> 01:43:33,080
You silly goose!

1154
01:44:10,640 --> 01:44:12,560
How do I look?

1155
01:44:14,920 --> 01:44:16,000
You look beautiful.

1156
01:44:17,240 --> 01:44:18,200
Thank you.

1157
01:44:21,520 --> 01:44:22,600
Let me.

1158
01:44:32,840 --> 01:44:37,040
My brother’s coming, I guess I wanted to look nice.

1159
01:44:42,000 --> 01:44:43,920
Okay, your brother’s coming, we get it…

1160
01:44:44,560 --> 01:44:46,120
but I’ll get jealous, you know.

1161
01:44:46,240 --> 01:44:49,720
Are you just looking for an excuse to be jealous?

1162
01:44:51,200 --> 01:44:52,480
Maybe.

1163
01:44:59,880 --> 01:45:01,760
My love is enough for everyone.

1164
01:45:03,080 --> 01:45:04,280
Hmm.

1165
01:45:09,360 --> 01:45:10,720
I can’t share you, sorry.

1166
01:45:20,680 --> 01:45:21,960
You two will get along.

1167
01:45:23,800 --> 01:45:28,040
I think so too. I’m also quite excited.

1168
01:45:30,000 --> 01:45:32,080
Love overcomes every obstacle.

1169
01:45:33,640 --> 01:45:37,440
Our love will too. I know it.

1170
01:45:47,480 --> 01:45:48,840
I can’t let you go.

1171
01:45:55,040 --> 01:45:56,160
I won’t let you go…

1172
01:46:16,920 --> 01:46:19,680
Great, everyone’s hiding in their corners,

1173
01:46:20,120 --> 01:46:21,880
and I’m the one answering the door!

1174
01:46:22,400 --> 01:46:24,280
Look at the new order of this house!

1175
01:46:37,080 --> 01:46:39,600
Oh, come on! What is this!

1176
01:46:40,360 --> 01:46:44,600
What are you doing here? Get out of my house!

1177
01:46:45,520 --> 01:46:48,440
I wouldn’t have come if I hadn’t been invited, Mrs. Nermin!

1178
01:46:48,880 --> 01:46:50,360
I'll go.

1179
01:46:53,480 --> 01:46:54,760
Burak…

1180
01:46:57,120 --> 01:46:59,720
come in, son. This is your home too.

1181
01:47:01,480 --> 01:47:04,560
What? And why don’t I know about this!

1182
01:47:10,720 --> 01:47:13,400
This is my home and my children’s home, Haydar Effendi!

1183
01:47:16,000 --> 01:47:17,400
Doesn’t look like it.

1184
01:47:18,080 --> 01:47:21,440
Honestly, this house is pretty confusing lately.

1185
01:47:22,000 --> 01:47:23,600
Feels like it’s ours these days!

1186
01:47:26,640 --> 01:47:27,960
Enough! That’s enough.

1187
01:47:31,560 --> 01:47:33,040
I invited Burak.

1188
01:47:40,640 --> 01:47:44,480
If he’s part of this family, he should live here too.

1189
01:47:45,720 --> 01:47:47,040
Oh really!

1190
01:47:47,640 --> 01:47:50,640
Since when you are the one making decisions in this house?

1191
01:47:53,840 --> 01:47:55,200
Listen, Mercan!

1192
01:47:56,640 --> 01:47:58,280
Mercan is the lady of this house.

1193
01:47:59,200 --> 01:48:01,360
She has every right to make decisions.

1194
01:48:12,240 --> 01:48:14,040
You did the right thing, dear.

1195
01:48:17,120 --> 01:48:20,040
Burak, son, you can take Murat’s room.

1196
01:48:20,800 --> 01:48:21,960
Wait!

1197
01:48:23,200 --> 01:48:27,440
Absolutely not! Never! You’ve all lost your minds!

1198
01:48:29,000 --> 01:48:30,640
Why not?

1199
01:48:30,880 --> 01:48:34,560
I’ll move my hobby room, Mrs. Nermin, no problem…

1200
01:48:42,920 --> 01:48:44,480
What do you want now?

1201
01:48:45,480 --> 01:48:47,040
I just sent it!

1202
01:48:49,360 --> 01:48:50,720
Okay.

1203
01:48:53,800 --> 01:48:56,080
Mercan, how could you do this to your brother?

1204
01:48:57,840 --> 01:48:58,880
And you, Haydar?

1205
01:49:04,600 --> 01:49:06,600
Murat is turning in his grave right now.

1206
01:49:15,200 --> 01:49:16,440
Shame on you.

1207
01:49:17,080 --> 01:49:18,520
Shame on you both.

1208
01:49:24,800 --> 01:49:26,120
I shouldn’t have come…

1209
01:49:26,520 --> 01:49:28,160
I didn’t want to disrupt anyone.

1210
01:49:28,400 --> 01:49:30,160
-I should just leave. -No.

1211
01:49:30,560 --> 01:49:33,200
Burak, please.

1212
01:49:34,520 --> 01:49:37,760
Try to understand my mom too. She’ll get used to it.

1213
01:49:39,920 --> 01:49:41,280
We all will.

1214
01:49:46,560 --> 01:49:49,960
If we welcome someone under this roof, no one gets to send them away.

1215
01:49:50,800 --> 01:49:52,320
Go to your room and settle in.

1216
01:49:53,920 --> 01:49:54,960
Okay.

1217
01:50:15,680 --> 01:50:18,160
-Ow! -Çiçek?

1218
01:50:24,360 --> 01:50:25,720
How did you do that?

1219
01:50:36,240 --> 01:50:37,680
It’s okay.

1220
01:50:45,240 --> 01:50:46,440
Does it hurt?

1221
01:50:47,160 --> 01:50:48,320
No.

1222
01:50:51,360 --> 01:50:52,880
I can’t stand seeing you hurt…

1223
01:50:54,240 --> 01:50:55,560
Thank you.

1224
01:50:56,560 --> 01:50:58,000
Are you alright?

1225
01:51:09,040 --> 01:51:10,400
Malik…

1226
01:51:14,320 --> 01:51:19,200
My love… it’s bigger than my anger or my pain.

1227
01:51:20,320 --> 01:51:22,280
I can’t let you go…

1228
01:51:23,040 --> 01:51:26,560
Çiçek! My flower… I’m not letting you go either…

1229
01:51:27,520 --> 01:51:30,840
I’d give up my life before I give up on you.

1230
01:51:33,080 --> 01:51:37,640
Look, I’ll never keep secrets from you again.

1231
01:51:38,400 --> 01:51:40,160
Never! I learned my lesson!

1232
01:51:40,680 --> 01:51:44,240
Nothing like this will happen. I swear. I Promise.

1233
01:51:44,640 --> 01:51:46,920
Yes. You have to, Malik.

1234
01:51:47,120 --> 01:51:49,280
If you ever hide something from me again…

1235
01:51:49,360 --> 01:51:52,240
it’ll be the last secret you ever hide. Just so you know.

1236
01:51:52,320 --> 01:51:58,040
And, I can face anything but only with someone I trust.

1237
01:51:59,080 --> 01:52:00,440
It won't happen again.

1238
01:52:00,560 --> 01:52:02,160
I promise, my love.

1239
01:52:23,240 --> 01:52:26,680
I can't stand being away from from you.

1240
01:52:27,440 --> 01:52:28,640
Me neither.

1241
01:52:31,040 --> 01:52:32,240
I love you so much.

1242
01:52:32,360 --> 01:52:33,600
I love you too.

1243
01:52:51,400 --> 01:52:52,600
Where were you, dear?

1244
01:52:52,680 --> 01:52:54,520
You call me here and don't show up…

1245
01:52:55,560 --> 01:52:57,000
There's something important.

1246
01:52:57,320 --> 01:52:58,720
That’s why I called you.

1247
01:53:00,000 --> 01:53:02,360
The realtor couldn’t reach you, so he called me.

1248
01:53:02,920 --> 01:53:05,600
You’re looking for a house… What’s going on, brother?

1249
01:53:06,120 --> 01:53:07,360
What's this about?

1250
01:53:07,640 --> 01:53:09,080
That’s your big issue?

1251
01:53:13,080 --> 01:53:16,120
Since when do I report my investments to you?

1252
01:53:17,880 --> 01:53:19,640
Your realtor mentioned a woman…

1253
01:53:20,480 --> 01:53:22,320
She said you’re buying it for her?

1254
01:53:22,480 --> 01:53:25,520
Doesn’t sound like an investment to me…

1255
01:53:27,800 --> 01:53:29,520
I said it’s an investment.

1256
01:53:30,360 --> 01:53:31,960
Why are you questioning me, sis?

1257
01:53:33,280 --> 01:53:36,680
I’m not. I was just curious.

1258
01:53:40,440 --> 01:53:42,240
There’s nothing to be curious about.

1259
01:53:45,120 --> 01:53:46,560
I’m buying it for Mercan.

1260
01:53:51,680 --> 01:53:54,320
So we’ll have a place to live together in the future.

1261
01:53:57,720 --> 01:54:00,960
Mercan is married, brother.

1262
01:54:02,320 --> 01:54:04,440
-And now-- -You think I don’t know that?

1263
01:54:05,760 --> 01:54:06,840
Huh?

1264
01:54:07,320 --> 01:54:09,160
Listen, I still have hope.

1265
01:54:10,280 --> 01:54:12,120
That house will keep that hope alive.

1266
01:54:12,520 --> 01:54:14,440
Alright? Don’t question it any further.

1267
01:54:15,520 --> 01:54:19,520
Brother! Stop hoping. It’s over.

1268
01:54:21,080 --> 01:54:22,680
Demet…

1269
01:54:25,120 --> 01:54:26,480
We’ll see about that.

1270
01:54:41,640 --> 01:54:44,080
It didn’t go as badly as I expected.

1271
01:54:45,320 --> 01:54:47,040
We got off easy.

1272
01:54:48,280 --> 01:54:50,080
Everyone will get used to it.

1273
01:54:50,720 --> 01:54:52,360
My mom too.

1274
01:55:48,440 --> 01:55:50,160
Enough of that. You’ll get dizzy.

1275
01:56:02,960 --> 01:56:04,320
Faster.

1276
01:56:04,760 --> 01:56:06,280
No. That’s enough.

1277
01:56:10,880 --> 01:56:12,320
Come on, faster.

1278
01:56:14,040 --> 01:56:16,320
You won’t let me fall, I know.

1279
01:56:21,480 --> 01:56:22,920
Of course I won’t.

1280
01:56:31,000 --> 01:56:33,280
Faster. Don’t be scared.

1281
01:56:33,720 --> 01:56:35,560
I’m braver than you think.

1282
01:56:37,640 --> 01:56:39,280
I know that part.

1283
01:57:31,680 --> 01:57:34,840
-Any news? -I found something important, Haydar.

1284
01:57:34,920 --> 01:57:35,800
Tell me.

1285
01:57:35,880 --> 01:57:42,240
Ateş Karahan secretly had Tahir Aslan’s parents’ graves opened.

1286
01:57:42,720 --> 01:57:45,960
Spent a fortune to keep it quiet.

1287
01:57:46,520 --> 01:57:51,160
What? He opened Tahir Aslan’s parents’ graves?

1288
01:57:52,280 --> 01:57:53,520
That’s the name.

1289
01:57:56,400 --> 01:57:59,080
Okay, but what could he possibly have to do with them?

1290
01:58:00,080 --> 01:58:01,840
Wait…

1291
01:58:03,440 --> 01:58:05,320
Was my first thought right?

1292
01:58:06,760 --> 01:58:08,760
But Cevat said he was dead.

1293
01:58:12,800 --> 01:58:15,360
Then why open Tahir’s parents’ graves?

1294
01:58:21,280 --> 01:58:22,720
Or…

1295
01:58:26,320 --> 01:58:28,320
What’s wrong, Haydar? You look pale.

1296
01:58:32,080 --> 01:58:33,600
…or was Cevat wrong?

1297
01:58:35,800 --> 01:58:37,960
Did they leave him thinking he was dead?

1298
01:58:39,960 --> 01:58:41,680
Is Tahir Aslan still alive?

1299
01:58:43,520 --> 01:58:45,360
Is Ateş Karahan… Tahir Aslan?!

1300
01:58:49,280 --> 01:58:50,600
I know you.

1301
01:58:52,200 --> 01:58:55,160
Ateş, listen… What are you doing! Calm down!

1302
01:58:55,880 --> 01:58:57,360
I said kneel.

1303
01:58:58,040 --> 01:59:01,640
Please don’t… I never did anything to you, Ateş!…

1304
01:59:02,160 --> 01:59:03,560
Stop lying to me!

1305
01:59:03,640 --> 01:59:05,800
I kept my word in the deal we made.

1306
01:59:05,880 --> 01:59:09,640
I gave you my mansion, my company, even my daughter, My Mercan…

1307
01:59:10,640 --> 01:59:12,840
I’m going to kill you!

1308
01:59:13,120 --> 01:59:15,080
You’ve deserved this for a long time.

1309
01:59:16,560 --> 01:59:19,280
We found the grave Ateş keeps visiting.

1310
01:59:20,680 --> 01:59:22,720
Good… Whose is it?

1311
01:59:23,760 --> 01:59:26,280
A child’s grave. Eylül Aslan.

1312
01:59:29,960 --> 01:59:31,640
Tahir?

1313
01:59:33,840 --> 01:59:35,560
Tahir.

1314
02:00:19,720 --> 02:00:22,720
They say "don’t talk big"

1315
02:00:24,120 --> 02:00:28,040
but life makes you do everything.

1316
02:00:29,640 --> 02:00:31,600
Makes you love what you hated,

1317
02:00:32,200 --> 02:00:34,440
makes you run toward what you tried to escape.

1318
02:00:36,280 --> 02:00:37,880
Did you hate me that much?

1319
02:00:39,520 --> 02:00:41,240
I don’t know if it was hate.

1320
02:00:41,880 --> 02:00:43,120
Probably not.

1321
02:00:44,240 --> 02:00:46,960
I was getting pulled toward you.

1322
02:00:51,000 --> 02:00:52,520
But you also annoyed me a lot.

1323
02:00:54,120 --> 02:00:55,440
Now I get it.

1324
02:00:56,600 --> 02:01:01,920
Every time I tried to run from you, I’d end up right next to you.

1325
02:01:04,920 --> 02:01:06,480
So you were the one pulling me.

1326
02:01:07,480 --> 02:01:09,800
But you chased me like crazy. Admit it.

1327
02:01:10,520 --> 02:01:11,840
I admit it.

1328
02:01:14,160 --> 02:01:15,880
We’ve overcome so much.

1329
02:01:19,800 --> 02:01:22,240
I guess that’s what happens when you love someone.

1330
02:01:23,120 --> 02:01:25,600
You think you can get through anything.

1331
02:01:27,480 --> 02:01:29,280
I’ve never loved before.

1332
02:01:35,520 --> 02:01:37,080
So I don’t know…

1333
02:01:40,400 --> 02:01:42,160
I’m living this for the first time.

1334
02:02:03,040 --> 02:02:05,000
It’s the best place…

1335
02:02:07,600 --> 02:02:08,840
but also the hardest.

1336
02:02:13,520 --> 02:02:14,800
Me too.

1337
02:02:15,560 --> 02:02:17,000
We’re in the same place…

1338
02:02:27,680 --> 02:02:29,400
My love is huge, Mercan.

1339
02:02:32,240 --> 02:02:34,560
It’s a love that will last forever.

1340
02:02:37,520 --> 02:02:38,680
Mine too.

1341
02:02:40,720 --> 02:02:42,240
No matter what the ending is.

1342
02:02:45,800 --> 02:02:47,320
No matter what the ending is.

1343
02:02:56,000 --> 02:02:58,840
No one is innocent of a sin they haven’t been tested with.

1344
02:03:00,280 --> 02:03:01,320
If this is a test,

1345
02:03:02,960 --> 02:03:05,680
I’m ready to face the hardest ones for our love.

1346
02:03:10,560 --> 02:03:13,000
I trust myself and my heart.

1347
02:03:17,200 --> 02:03:19,240
But more than anything, I trust you, Ateş.

1348
02:03:20,400 --> 02:03:22,400
I’m ready to hear the truth.

1349
02:03:25,040 --> 02:03:25,920
Okay.

1350
02:03:30,960 --> 02:03:32,160
Mercan, I--

1351
02:03:36,400 --> 02:03:37,720
Excuse me.

1352
02:03:41,360 --> 02:03:43,960
-I’m not available, Aslı. -Ateş wait… Don’t hang up.

1353
02:03:44,040 --> 02:03:47,120
It’s important. I’m outside, I need help with an email.

1354
02:03:47,200 --> 02:03:49,560
-It’s urgent, The guy's waiting. -What email…?

1355
02:03:50,320 --> 02:03:51,920
For our partner in Italy.

1356
02:03:52,600 --> 02:03:54,920
You need to check something in the study…

1357
02:03:55,640 --> 02:03:56,760
Okay.

1358
02:03:59,640 --> 02:04:02,040
I'm sorry. I'll be back quickly. Wait here.

1359
02:04:19,080 --> 02:04:21,640
She says she’ll face the hardest tests for her love.

1360
02:04:21,960 --> 02:04:25,400
Fail this test and learn your place!

1361
02:04:26,360 --> 02:04:27,880
We’ll see!

1362
02:04:30,000 --> 02:04:31,640
"I trust myself…"

1363
02:05:04,400 --> 02:05:05,760
What is it, Mom?

1364
02:05:05,960 --> 02:05:07,760
What kind of tone is that, dear?

1365
02:05:08,680 --> 02:05:13,360
Forget me, what are you up to? You disappeared again…

1366
02:05:14,560 --> 02:05:16,720
I had things to do outside.

1367
02:05:17,360 --> 02:05:21,320
Your voice sounds tense, what’s going on? Are you okay?

1368
02:05:22,280 --> 02:05:25,840
No. I’m great actually.

1369
02:05:27,520 --> 02:05:29,840
Mercan will learn all the truth, Mom.

1370
02:05:31,040 --> 02:05:35,440
Don’t, Aslı! Don’t do anything stupid! I'm telling you not to!

1371
02:05:35,680 --> 02:05:38,000
In fact, I don’t even need to do anything.

1372
02:05:38,640 --> 02:05:40,840
Ateş is about to tell her everything anyway.

1373
02:05:42,120 --> 02:05:44,760
But if he tells her, it won’t help us.

1374
02:05:45,720 --> 02:05:47,960
If she hears it from him, she’ll forgive him.

1375
02:05:49,600 --> 02:05:52,560
But she’ll learn it from me in a much harsher way.

1376
02:05:54,320 --> 02:05:56,000
And she’ll never forgive.

1377
02:05:59,360 --> 02:06:01,320
Aslı! Aslı! Aslı!

1378
02:06:01,880 --> 02:06:03,080
Aslı!

1379
02:06:03,600 --> 02:06:07,480
Hurry to the mansion! Faster!

1380
02:06:08,240 --> 02:06:09,760
Hurry!

1381
02:06:20,480 --> 02:06:22,080
Nothing will happen to us.

1382
02:06:23,600 --> 02:06:27,680
I trust my love and I trust Ateş.

1383
02:06:29,920 --> 02:06:32,160
Let me introduce you to the truth…

1384
02:06:32,800 --> 02:06:34,560
then you can trust him if you want.

1385
02:06:35,000 --> 02:06:38,040
Aslı, please. Not today.

1386
02:06:38,640 --> 02:06:40,760
On the contrary. Today.

1387
02:06:42,400 --> 02:06:46,000
This is my first and last kindness to you, Mercan.

1388
02:06:52,840 --> 02:06:55,000
Since you want the truth,

1389
02:06:55,920 --> 02:06:58,160
if you trust your love so much,

1390
02:06:59,720 --> 02:07:02,600
take this key and look in the basement.

1391
02:07:05,160 --> 02:07:09,680
You’ll find everything there about Ateş Karahan, about us,

1392
02:07:10,560 --> 02:07:14,600
why we’re here, why we’re doing this to you…

1393
02:07:15,360 --> 02:07:18,080
all of it, with documents.

1394
02:07:23,440 --> 02:07:25,040
If you have the courage.

1395
02:07:27,200 --> 02:07:28,680
There’s no need.

1396
02:07:29,040 --> 02:07:30,920
We’ll handle it between us.

1397
02:07:31,160 --> 02:07:33,480
Ateş will tell me everything.

1398
02:07:34,360 --> 02:07:35,960
Sure…

1399
02:07:36,440 --> 02:07:39,600
but you know very well that’s not what the truth is.

1400
02:07:41,040 --> 02:07:43,880
Which version of the truth will he tell you?

1401
02:07:44,960 --> 02:07:46,800
How much of it?

1402
02:07:47,240 --> 02:07:51,000
In the end, how much can you trust a man who’s already lied once?

1403
02:07:52,640 --> 02:07:54,160
What lie?

1404
02:07:58,320 --> 02:08:00,040
Go and see.

1405
02:08:02,480 --> 02:08:03,720
Of course, if you want.

1406
02:08:04,760 --> 02:08:08,360
If the truth cuts you even a little, if you’d rather close your eyes,

1407
02:08:09,320 --> 02:08:14,160
if you’re going to do what’s convenient… that’s up to you.

1408
02:08:16,400 --> 02:08:20,400
But wouldn't you want to know who the man you love really is…

1409
02:08:21,640 --> 02:08:23,440
Everything is unfiltered down there.

1410
02:08:24,080 --> 02:08:25,840
Ice‑cold truth.

1411
02:08:27,800 --> 02:08:30,320
You won’t be cold when you enter that room, Mercan.

1412
02:08:33,880 --> 02:08:35,120
You’ll turn to ice.

1413
02:09:32,240 --> 02:09:33,360
Whoops!

1414
02:09:33,440 --> 02:09:35,560
Pardon me. After you, honey.

1415
02:09:37,240 --> 02:09:38,920
Yeah.

1416
02:09:43,520 --> 02:09:45,560
Surprise!!!

1417
02:09:53,600 --> 02:09:54,920
We got married!!!

1418
02:10:04,520 --> 02:10:05,920
Bro… brother…

1419
02:10:06,440 --> 02:10:07,480
Yeah?

1420
02:10:08,840 --> 02:10:10,200
What a nonsense!

1421
02:10:13,760 --> 02:10:15,280
This is not a theater?

1422
02:10:15,760 --> 02:10:18,120
Go change your clothes!

1423
02:10:21,400 --> 02:10:22,760
Um, Mom…

1424
02:10:24,480 --> 02:10:25,600
Let me take it, love.

1425
02:10:25,680 --> 02:10:27,080
Here you go, love.

1426
02:10:27,960 --> 02:10:30,080
Mom, we're not acting.

1427
02:10:30,760 --> 02:10:32,240
We got married.

1428
02:13:47,200 --> 02:13:48,320
What are our…

1429
02:13:50,720 --> 02:13:54,040
What are our photos doing here?

1430
02:14:51,120 --> 02:14:52,560
These files…

1431
02:14:53,040 --> 02:14:54,560
What are these?

1432
02:15:16,360 --> 02:15:18,120
Everyone has a file.

1433
02:15:29,200 --> 02:15:30,440
My dad…

1434
02:15:49,160 --> 02:15:51,640
Everything about my dad is here…

1435
02:16:24,280 --> 02:16:25,480
Mercan Yıldırım.

1436
02:16:40,480 --> 02:16:45,760
"Mercan's biggest weakness is her kindness."

1437
02:16:46,240 --> 02:16:49,520
"Easy to manipulate."

1438
02:16:53,160 --> 02:16:57,640
"Play on her mercy, her pure heart."

1439
02:16:58,840 --> 02:17:04,720
"To break her from her family, exposing Haydar’s dirt is enough."

1440
02:17:05,680 --> 02:17:11,240
"If the family turns on each other, they’re easier to destroy."

1441
02:17:13,120 --> 02:17:14,440
What?

1442
02:17:22,840 --> 02:17:26,080
These photos… What are they?

1443
02:17:26,680 --> 02:17:28,720
What kind of game is this?

1444
02:18:24,720 --> 02:18:27,000
I’m either your savior or your executioner.

1445
02:18:27,080 --> 02:18:28,760
Who knows?

1446
02:18:32,760 --> 02:18:34,760
It was all his plan!

1447
02:18:35,320 --> 02:18:38,720
But what about our love?

1448
02:18:40,520 --> 02:18:42,040
Our love?

1449
02:20:31,880 --> 02:20:33,280
You?

1450
02:20:38,320 --> 02:20:41,480
That's me…

1451
02:20:45,200 --> 02:20:47,120
Tahir.

1452
02:21:10,480 --> 02:21:11,760
Tahir.

1453
02:21:17,840 --> 02:21:19,200
Tahir.

1454
02:21:31,280 --> 02:21:32,720
Tahir.
